title: barbecued brisket
directions: Generously sprinkle entire brisket with salt.
Pour liquid smoke over meat in cooking pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before cooking, sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake fat side up at 275° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours until very tender.
Remove meat from oven, pour on barbecue sauce and let cool in pan.
Slice when cold.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate until next day.
Reheat when ready to serve.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Mix together.
Keep in refrigerator until serving time.

title: tropical ice
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze.
After slightly frozen, beat or stir.
It may then be poured in ice trays or I leave mine in same container (pitcher).
When ready to serve, place 2 or 3 cubes or spoonfuls in glass and pour ginger ale or 7-Up to fill up glass.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix ingredients to use as the dip for Pronto Pups.
Dry hot dogs on paper towel; push a stick (obtained from meat man) into hot dog to form handle.
Dip into batter and fry in deep grease until golden brown.
Optional:
Serve with catsup and mustard.

title: pretzel fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Dry the chicken with paper toweling.
Mix eggs and milk well.
Place the finely crushed pretzels in a paper sack. Dip chicken in the egg-milk mixture, then place in crushed pretzels and shake until coated.
Drop into 350° vegetable oil and fry until a rich golden brown.
Place the fried pieces of chicken on aluminum foil in a large flat baking pan and bake at 300° for about 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cajun ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces.
Combine seasonings together well and rub on all surfaces of ribs.
Place ribs on covered grill over indirect heat and grill for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 4.
Preparation Time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
90 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add
eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture alternating with milk; add almond and vanilla.
Pour into 3 x 5 x 10-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: *carrot cake frosting
directions: Cream well and mix all ingredients together.
Keep cake in the refrigerator.

title: breadsticks
directions: Cut buns lengthwise.
Place very close on cookie sheet.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Spoon mixture over each stick. Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese casserole bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and yeast; stir to dissolve yeast. Add sugar, butter and salt; stir until butter is melted.
Stir in 3 cups of the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and cheese; mix well.
Pour batter into well-buttered 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Cover with waxed paper; let rise in warm place (85°), until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: mrs. mount's chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir into stuffing mix.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of 1/3 stuffing and 1/2 chicken.
Pour cream of celery soup mixed with 1/2 can of water and 1/2 can chicken broth. Place next layer of 1/3 stuffing and 1/2 chicken.
Pour over cream of chicken soup mixed with 1/2 can of chicken broth and 1/2 can of water.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Pour 1/2 can of chicken broth over all (or freeze and defrost and add whole can of broth to top).
Bake at 350°, covered, for 40 minutes.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Put sliced potatoes in casserole dish, then add sliced kielbasa on top.
Heat soup and water.
Add cheese to soup until orange.
The more cheese the better.

title: luscious chocolate almond sauce
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, combine chocolate chips, cream, butter and salt, stirring constantly until smooth; remove from heat.
Stir in almonds and liqueur; cool slightly.
Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts.
Refrigerate leftover sauce; reheat before serving.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: texas style steak
directions: Trim excess fat from the steak.
Combine seasoning and lightly rub both sides of steak with spice mixture.
Spray meat generously on both sides with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spray unheated grill rack with nonstick cooking spray. Place steak on grill and cook 5 minutes on each side for medium or until desired doneness.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients, pour over warm carrots.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Arrange unpeeled potatoes in pan.
Stir together the rest of ingredients.
Pour over the potatoes and toss to coat.
Bake uncovered about 25 minutes or until brown and tender.
Stir and turn once or twice.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Mix horseradish and cream cheese with a fork until of spreading consistency.
Spread thin layer of mixture on round slices of dried beef.
Roll, cut in half and secure with toothpick.

title: beefy quiche
directions: Bake pie crust for 5 minutes at 450° or as directed on package.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain well. Mix eggs and soup. Place hamburger in pie crust.
Add egg and soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bring to boil, milk, sugar and margarine. Add eggs and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Whip.
Place in baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels (which have been crushed with a rolling pin), oleo and 4 1/2 teaspoons sugar together; spread out in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°, then cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar well.
Fold in whipped topping, spread on pretzels and chill in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large heavy skillet, heat oil until hot but not smoking. Add garlic and saute until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, parsley and oregano.
Simmer 35 to 40 minutes, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked and drained pasta of your choice and toss with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt oleo and cool.
Chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into three 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 375° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bourbon brownies
directions: Bake the brownies according to package directions.
While still hot, pour bourbon on top.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and pour into buttered 3-quart rectangular dish.
Sprinkle paprika and poultry seasoning on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil during baking.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake and bone chicken breasts.
Saute onion in oleo.
Pour in Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and add chicken broth.
(I use broth from chicken and add Swanson chicken broth as needed.)
Simmer all of this for 30 minutes.

title: brunch bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
In small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese, sesame seed and basil.
Add about 1/3 of mixture to greased pan.

Lift and turn pan to coat sides and bottom. Place 10 frozen rolls in pan; drizzle with 1/2 the margarine. Sprinkle 1/2 of remaining cheese mixture and bacon bits on top. Add remaining rolls, drizzle with remaining margarine and sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture.
Cover.
Let rolls thaw and rise overnight, 12 to 24 hours, in refrigerator.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add melted butter.
Add dry ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amaretto slushes
directions: Stir sugar and instant tea into boiling water until dissolved. Add orange juice, lemonade, water and Amaretto. Stir well. Pour into freezer container (gallon ice cream container works perfect). Freeze for 5 to 7 days prior to wanting to use. Serve semi-frozen.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a skillet, brown beef and chili powder.
Spoon off fat.

title: corned beef patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour. Form into patties; roll lightly in flour and fry in hot oil or butter or margarine until browned. Serve on toast or a bed of grits.
(Bahamian Cookery Cookbook.) |Anonymous

title: parmesan potato rounds
directions: Pour butter into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
In a plastic bag, combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Shake a few potato slices at a time in the bag to coat with the flour mixture. Place potatoes in a single layer over the butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn slices and sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Bake 30 minutes more or until tender.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix at night. Refrigerate in pan lined with waxed paper. Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice thin and bake until done.
(No time given; old recipe!
Watch.)

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream cheese and margarine.
Blend or stir in flour.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Mash down with fork. Sprinkle with cayenne to taste.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Store in airtight container to make crisp.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips and dressing, ahead of time.
Right before serving, crunch the bag of chips and then add these and the bottle of dressing to original mixture.

title: heart association's chicken salad casserole
directions: Simmer green pepper in water until nearly tender; drain. Combine milk with mayonnaise.
Add pimento, green pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts, chicken and salt.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings at about 260 calories each.

title: hamburger-cornbread casserole
directions: In lightly greased skillet, saute onion and pepper. Then place in a 2-quart casserole. Brown hamburger and mix it and the tomato sauce and beans in the casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: onion salad
directions: Place onion and soda in lukewarm water and let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Then crisp onions by allowing them to stand in ice water, changing water several times.
Drain and dry thoroughly.
Add vinegar, sugar and seasoning.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and dry thoroughly.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with mayonnaise. Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh herb vinaigrette
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container.
About 1 cup dressing; 60 calories per tablespoon.

title: incredibles
directions: Pour melted butter over graham cracker crumbs in large bowl; mix well.
Add peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix well. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt chocolate chips in small saucepan.
Pour over top.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Note:
Do not use light or fat-free sour cream because it will curdle during baking.
Shredded cooked chicken can be used instead of ground beef.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Add flour until dough is stiff. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer bottom of casserole with Doritos.
Combine mushroom and chicken soups and tomatoes; add chicken.
Layer chicken mixture (all of it); add a layer of Doritos.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: pastel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Divide batter into 2 bowls. Add lime gelatin to one bowl and lemon to the other. Stir through. Pour each into separate wax paper-lined greased and floured 9-inch round cake pan. Bake 28 to 30 minutes (until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean). Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool on wire racks. Place lime cake layer on serving plate. Spread with 1/2 tub whipped topping. Top with lemon cake layer. Frost cake with remaining whipped topping. Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve. Yield: 12 servings.

title: cheesy nachos
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Place meat in microwave dish and add tomatoes and cheese.
Microwave on HIGH until cheese is completely melted.
Serve hot over chips.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: In a large bowl mix dry ingredients first, then add milk, applesauce, oil, eggs and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour batter into one large greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle topping over the batter and bake at 350° until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Place clean beans in water. Bring to a boil in heavy pot. Add next 6 ingredients. Stir well. Lower heat to simmer. Place bacon on top. Cover and cook for 6 to 8 hours. Add small amount of water occasionally, if needed. Serves 4 to 6.4

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and beaten egg yolks together in a double boiler. Add Carnation milk. Fill to top of double boiler with regular milk. Cover and cook until filling becomes a medium thickness.	Add butter and vanilla to hot filling. Let cool. Pour over your bananas and wafers in a square casserole dish. Top with meringue. Bake until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad supreme
directions: Rinse spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients together except the cucumbers and tomatoes.
Add Italian seasoning according to taste. Let salad marinate overnight, then add cucumbers and tomatoes the next day.
Mix well, stirring from the bottom.
(Dressing will settle to the bottom of bowl; make sure salad is stirred from the bottom just before serving.)

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in airtight container.
To make tea, place as much of mixture as you like in bottom of cup and fill with hot water, or mix cold water for iced tea.

title: bavarian apple cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the first one-third cup sugar, the margarine or butter, shortening and 1/4 teaspoon of vanilla on medium speed of an electric mixer until combined.
Blend in flour and salt until crumbly.
Pat onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Place apple slices in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix oil, water and egg.
Combine and beat by hand for 50 strokes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately spread with Marshmallow Fluff.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Break candy bars into pieces and place on top.
Return to oven for about 2 minutes to allow chocolate to melt.
Spread with knife.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: In a large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine cheeses.
Spread 1 cup of bean mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 1/4 of noodles on top.
Top with 1 1/2 cups bean mixture and 1/4 cheese mixture.
Repeat 3 more times.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Top with sour cream and chopped cilantro.

title: good sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill buns with mixture.
Set each sandwich on a square of aluminum foil.
Wrap foil around sandwich, leaving an opening about the size of a half dollar at the top.
Place on tray.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour, making sure cheese is melted.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and saute.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings. Mash together and fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza pies
directions: Roll each biscuit out individually, then spread each with pizza sauce.
On one side of each biscuit, layer all veggies and top with cheese.
Then take other side and fold over top of the veggies. Close by using fork to press together.
Place each on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with butter on top and bake about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Slowly cook onions in oleo until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 5 minutes.
This sauce is very good for chicken or pork.
I often add browned spareribs and simmer for about an hour.
Excellent!
Recipe easily doubles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and then top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cinnamon punch
directions: Heat cider, cinnamon candies and allspice to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove allspice.
Stir in honey.
Makes 24 servings.

title: panhandle chicken wings
directions: Remove the tips and cut wings at the joint so you have 2 small pieces from each.
Bake wings at 350° while you prepare the sauce. Remove chicken wings from the oven and pour off any fat.
Cover with sauce.
Loosely cover pan with foil and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato candy(this is a very old recipe)
directions: Boil potato until tender.
Rice it to obtain a very smooth mixture.
Mix with powdered sugar until thick enough to knead. Knead well and roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Spread peanut butter 1/4-inch thick.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Slice.

title: broccoli creamed corn bake
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain well.
Beat eggs, melt butter and add corn, onion and broccoli.
For topping, use crouton crumbs or bacon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Best when
topped with white icing.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and put into a 4 quart casserole dish. Add mushroom soup. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for an hour. Add cheese and bake 15 minutes or until tender (covered).

title: root vegetables
directions: Wash and trim potatoes (do not peel), carrots, parsnips, sweet potatoes (unpeeled) and turnips.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add vegetables to boiling water.
Cover and cook 7 minutes.
Slice onions and shallots; transfer cooked vegetables to bowl and cover loosely with foil.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and shallots.
Saute 2 minutes. Drain and discard any liquid from bowl.
Add vegetables to skillet; add oil, sugar and salt.
Cook. Stir frequently from bottom of skillet 10 to 15 minutes until brown and tender.
Add pepper.
Sprinkle parsley on top before serving.
Serves 4.

title: million dollar spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Brown beef.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cheeses and sour cream.
Add onions.
Use 2-quart dish.
Spread 1/2 noodles.
Cover with sauce and cheeses in layers and repeat with second half of noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix
well,
then add to yeast mixture hot water, oil, sugar, eggs
and
salt.
Add flour and wheat germ. Chill in refrigerator
until firm, about 2 hours. Shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at
for 10 minutes or freeze raw rolls for later use.

title: pea casserole
directions: Line "buttered" dish with a layer of crumbled cheese crackers (Cheddar).
Drain 1 can of peas with pearl onions, layer over crackers.
Put another layer of crumbled cheese crackers.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce to 1 can mushroom soup with 1 cup milk.
Pour over mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: swiss steak sauterne
directions: Pound steak.
Cut into 6 serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour.
In heavy skillet, brown meat in heated oil along with mushrooms and onions.
Add wine and juice from mushrooms.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and egg quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle hard-cooked eggs in bottom of pie crust.
Top with ham and cheeses.
Combine beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over filling.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet until mixture is set, about 35 minutes.
Let stand before serving.

title: mock mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes; drain well.
Measure juice and add same amount of water to pulp.
Scald mixture and drain off liquid.
Repeat this process twice, adding fresh water, scalding and draining.
Add next 4 ingredients to pulp and cook until mixture is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until mixture is thick.
Can hot.

title: bologna
directions: Mix all together thoroughly and let cure for 48 hours.
Stuff into jars and pressure can for 35 minutes or cold pack for 2 1/2 hours.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown onions in butter and garlic salt.
Put in large pot along with tomatoes, corned beef, beans, Worcestershire sauce and red and black pepper; salt to taste.
Add cooked potatoes and then corn last.
Cook on low 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: peanut butter streusel microwave brownies
directions: Combine oats,
powdered
sugar
and
peanut butter in a medium-sized bowl;
mix together until the mixture is crumbly. Combine mix,
eggs
and
mayonnaise in bowl.
Spray microwave-safe 10 x
x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Spread batter in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with peanut-butter topping. Microwave at
half
power
for 5 minutes, turning once. Turn again. Microwave
at
full
power
(100%) for 4 minutes. Remove dish
to wire
rack to cool completely before cutting. Makes 18 brownies.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese (softened) and Cool Whip together.
Stir in pineapple juice and powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan and add two strips of bacon on the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce snack cakes
directions: Cream margarine; gradually
add
sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric
mixer.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Stir soda and vanilla into applesauce.

title: snack mix(big batch)
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in shallow pan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over snack mix and stir to coat well.
Heat approximately 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. If desired, place on absorbent toweling before storing in tins.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco, egg and milk.
Combine salt, flour, soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: pasta and cheese toss
directions: Prepare tomatoes, basil and garlic while pasta is cooking as per package.
Drain pasta; mix in Mozzarella and toss.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Toss thoroughly.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.

Cover for 2 minutes. Uncover and cook, without stirring, to hard boil stage (254°). Pour in steady fine stream over egg whites and continue beating with electric or rotary beater until mixture holds it shape and loses its gloss.
Stir in vanilla extract and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: lemon banana refresher
directions: Combine drink mix, banana, and water in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add crushed ice and blend until ice is almost melted. Makes 2 cups or 4 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan. Add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and clear.
Cool.

title: squash relish(yields 6 pints)
directions: Coarsely grind squash, onions and bell peppers; add salt.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, drain.
Wash in cold water, using a fine wire colander.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients; bring to boil.
Add relish mixture; let return to boil and boil about 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: turkey with squash dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to directions; cool on wire rack.
Mix with herb dressing.
Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add salt, pepper, cheese, eggs, squash, sage, sauteed onions and celery to bread mixture.
Add broth.
Remove giblets from turkey; rinse turkey with cold water and pat dry. Sprinkle cavity of turkey with salt.
Put stuffing into turkey. Brush turkey with vegetable oil.
Cook at 325° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours, covered.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice enough potatoes to cover 1 inch deep on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour over potatoes.
Lay seasoned pork chops over potato mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovering foil last 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onions and green pepper; crumble cheese, corn bread and white bread.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put it in a cake pan and pour catsup on top.
Smooth with spoon and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Before pouring mixture into pie shell, be sure to stick a few fork holes in the bottom.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large sauce pan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain. Discard all but two tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings.
Cook stirring until thickened.
Serves 4-6.

title: unbaked drop cookies(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate in 200° oven for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven and add to other ingredients.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
When cool, they're ready to eat.

title: rice fritters
directions: Cook rice; let cool.
Add eggs to rice; mix well.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon into very hot oil; fry until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add salt and vanilla.
Mash bananas and add soda to them.
Mix nuts with flour and add to butter-banana mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks.

title: spinach-carrot stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Saute carrot, spinach and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine. Salt and pepper and add Parmesan.
Place mixture in center of each chicken breast; fold in half or roll closed.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in separate bowl and add bread crumbs.
Mix together and pat mixture over the top of chicken. Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or unti lightly brown.

title: pork chop mexicana
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt.
Brown in oil on both sides.
Drain. Place chops in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle rice around chops.
Combine water, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and salt.
Pour over chops and rice, cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese and top with green pepper. Cover and bake for 15 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce, salt and black pepper.
Mix cornbread and pour half in bottom of casserole dish.
Add layer of meat.
Top with remaining cornbread.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: truly mexican salsa
directions: Combine all finely chopped vegetables.
Stir in seasonings. Marinate 15 minutes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine sugar or Sweet 'N Low, water, egg whites and cream of tartar in top of double boiler; beat at high speed for 1 minute. Set over simmering water in the bottom of a double boiler. Continue to beat at high speed for 4 to 5 minutes, until soft. Remove from heat when soft.
Add vanilla to frosting; continue at high speed for 1 to 2 minutes, or until thick.
Use 2 1/2 tablespoons per portion when frosting.

title: winnie's brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
In large glass or Tupperware bowl, microwave butter and unsweetened chocolate at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir mixture until smooth, then stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with wooden spoon until blended.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into pan and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan, then cut into bars.

title: potato dumpling
directions: Add eggs, salt, sugar and nutmeg to taste to potatoes and mix well.
Add flour; flour is added just before you spoon it into soup.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and drain.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with chips.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: lemon butter
directions: Squeeze lemon and grate rind into saucepan.
Mix all other ingredients together, except butter, and cook until it comes to a boil, stirring often.
Continue cooking until it thickens.
When thick, take from stove and stir in butter.
Keep stirring.
Don't let it stick.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in boiling water in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add soup mix and rice.
Cover with chicken and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or 3 hours at 225°.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika if desired.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash cauliflower, broccoli and onions.
Cut in small pieces. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Mix well to make a smooth sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir well.
Add celery seed, salt and pepper.
Chill well before serving.

title: easter bread
directions: Put sugar, butter, eggs, milk, salt and yeast cake in a saucepan; heat (do not boil) until warm and yeast is dissolved. Pour into flour; knead dough until it comes away from pan (add raisins, if desired).
Cover; put in warm place.
Let raise until double in bulk.
Punch down; let raise again.
Grease pan and fill halfway.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: virginia apple pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and cover with lattice top.
Bake at 375° until set, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: diabetic nut cake(sugar free)
directions: Add sweetener with beaten egg, butter and vanilla.
Proceed as for regular cake.
Turn into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan lined with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
This cake freezes well.

title: fancy brussels sprouts
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water, parsley, sugar and salt to the boil. Add sprouts. Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender; drain. Add butter and water chestnuts; heat through. Yield: 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Dot with butter.
Cover with cheese and ham.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
Pour over bread, cheese and ham.
Let set overnight or 8 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife test in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Brown meat; drain in a colander.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and parsley in olive oil.
Add mushrooms.
Add ground beef.
Add thyme, salt and pepper.
Add pecan halves and mix.
Lower fire, cover and continue cooking 10 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Fry bacon; remove from grease.
Crumble and save.
Fry okra until all slickness is gone.
Remove from grease and add to bacon. Fry onions, celery, garlic, green onions, green pepper and parsley until limp.
Add chili powder and mix well.
Now add everything up to and including 6 cups hot water.
Check list. Cover and cook slowly until mixture is thick, about 1 hour.
Add raw, cleaned shrimp and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add file, curry and olives.
Leave out last 4 ingredients to freeze sauce.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it is done.
Debone and cut in bite-sized pieces.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Spread broccoli in baking dish; then spread chicken on top of that.
Prepare sauce and pour over this.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Place slices of American cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese croutons for soup
directions: Beat
eggs,
adding
cheese,
salt, pepper, parsley and garlic.
Add
small
amounts of flour needed to make a pancake batter,
not too thin or thick.
Drop by large spoons into hot oil in
frying pan.
Brown one side and then the other.
Cool and cut up into small squares.
Drop into hot soup.
If batter is too thick, thin out with milk.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well and pour into hot skillet, greased with 1/8 cup of Wesson oil.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: panned rabbit
directions: Divide the rabbit at the joint and stew until tender.
Butter a pan and lay the pieces over the bottom.
Beat the eggs.
Mix with the other ingredients and spread over the rabbit.
Set in a hot oven and bake until brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo in shallow baking dish.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Add milk at once. Stir just enough to blend ingredients.
Pour batter over melted oleo in baking dish.
Spoon peaches on top of batter.
Bake until golden brown.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in slow cooker with roast.
Cook on medium all night.
In morning, shred with fork and leave in cooker all day.
Serve on French bread or buns.

title: packsaddle pancakes
directions: Place dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix eggs, oil, buttermilk and yeast; stir well.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and stir until just blended.
Batter will be thick.
Cover lightly and keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at slightly lower temperature than usual pancakes.
This batter will keep up to 5 days in refrigerator.
May be thinned with milk.
Make 16 to 18 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: sausage bread
directions: Scramble sausage; saute onions and bell pepper. Grate cheese. Press each loaf into a rectangular shape. Layer cheese, sausage, onions and bell pepper and cheese. Butter top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: reese's cup bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread with melted chocolate chips.
Refrigerate at few minutes until firm (not hard).
Cut into desired size.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine wine vinegar, sugar, oil, onion and green pepper and mix well in a large bowl.
Drain and add to dressing green beans, waxed beans, kidney beans and garbanzo beans.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight before serving (the longer it marinates, the better it is).

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crescent roll salad
directions: Pat crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan and up the sides. Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Next spread the cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch mixture.
Put on lettuce and any vegetables that you like, topping with shredded cheese.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in solution of 3/4 cup salt to 1 gallon of water. Soak for 7 days. Drain and wash pickles and container. Cover with alum mixture (3 tablespoons alum to 1 quart water). Soak 24 hours, then drain and wash. Cover with vinegar and spices. Soak 24 hours. Drain and layer 3-inches of pickles and 3 cups sugar. Repeat layers.

title: pimiento cream sandwich spread
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, salt and mustard.
Combine with the evaporated milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Add cheese which has been grated.
Cook mixture in top of double boiler over boiling water until thickened and cheese melts.
Stir constantly while cooking, then removing from stove and add margarine, chopped pimiento and vinegar.
May be kept 2 or 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Combine flour and margarine in a mixing bowl until crumbly. Add remaining ingredients, using enough evaporated milk to hold mixture together.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Wash chicken breast; debone and cut into 1 to 2 inch strips, following the grain while cutting the meat.
Marinate in buttermilk overnight or for a few hours.
Beat egg until fluffy (can add a few drops of water).
Dip each strip in egg mixture, then shake each one in a small paper bag containing the flour, salt and pepper.
Deep fat fry at 250° to 300° until golden brown or in skillet with oil.
Drain on paper towel.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Mix noodles with turkey, eggs, mushrooms, celery, almonds and onions.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and toss with turkey mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
A good way to use leftover turkey.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pork chops dijon
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In small bowl, combine salad dressing, mustard and pepper, brush mixture on both sides of chops.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook chops, covered, over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn chops, add onion, cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more, or until meat is tender.
Top with onions and pan juices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: polynesian stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Set aside.
Combine rice, ham, chopped onion, coriander, ginger, salt and pepper.
Stuff cleaned peppers with rice mixture.
Place upright in a shallow pan.
Set aside.
Combine undrained pineapple, onion, green pepper and tomatoes in a pot.
Heat until boiling.
Add in cornstarch mixture.
Stir until thick.
Put the sauce in the pan with the stuffed peppers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Place shredded zucchini in a colander.
Mix with salt.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Using hands, squeeze the excess moisture from the zucchini.
Mix all ingredients.
Add zucchini and mix well (the stuffing will seem dry, but the zucchini will make more liquid when baked).
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve with chicken.

title: ground beef-biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Spoon into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper in bowl.
Pour over ground beef mixture. Arrange biscuits over top.
Bake at 450° until biscuits are golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mints
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Cut cream cheese into sugar.
Add flavoring and color.
Put powdered sugar on hands and knead mixture until color is even.
Press mixture into rubber molds.
Pop out and put on paper towel for a few minutes.
Store in airtight container with wax paper between layers.
These can be made up to 2 weeks in advance and put in freezer.
Makes approximately 200 mints.

title: chinese beef salad
directions: Blend all of the ingredients except noodles.
Add noodles just before serving.
In place of beef you can also use turkey, chicken or ham.

title: sweet potato banana casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until soft, drain and mash.
Add butter, nuts, coconut and sugar.
Mix well.
If dry, add orange juice or cream.
Place 1/2 of mixture in buttered casserole. Cover with bananas which have been mashed, then add remainder of potato mixture.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup of crushed corn flakes mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter and 1/4 cup brown sugar. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: springtime strawberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Spread on bottom of 9 by 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: chili
directions: In a large soup pot put onion, celery, and hamburger. Fry together until hamburger is lightly browned. Add a large diced tomato, tomato soup, salt, chili powder, sage, pepper and water. Heat for 2 hours, then add red kidney beans. Adjust salt to taste. Cayenne pepper can be added for a bit more "bite".

title: delicious banana bread
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar.
Cream well.
Blend in bananas and eggs.
Sift flour, flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk or sour milk, blending until well combined.
Fold in nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes one 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and margarine.
Add flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 400° for 35 minutes. Cool.

title: tilden cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time, beating well. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add lemon extract.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: come-back dipping sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Good as a dipping sauce for deep-fried foods such as chicken fingers.

title: peanut butter cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Mix thoroughly the peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg. Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake until set but not hard.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk for 7 minutes.
Take off of heat. Add peanut butter, marshmallows and nuts; stir.
Quickly add flour; stir and pour into greased pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all vegetables, salt, pepper and parsley flakes into pot with 2 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil; then turn heat down to low.
Put lid on pot and cook for 20-25 min.
Put milk and flour in a jar and shake up real good.
Pour into pot with vegetables. Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes and add to pot.
Continue cooking until cheese is melted.

title: ugly bean dip
directions: Clean, drain and chop specified ingredients and mix with dressing. Let chill at least 6 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, then add flour and roll out to 1/4 inch.
Cut or score in pie plate and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix butter, Crisco, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
In a separate bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; beat well.
Add M&M's and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: shrimp-rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat Butter Buds; add onion, mushrooms, bell pepper, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until rice is golden brown.
Put in Kitchen Bouquet.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and simmer.
Add shrimp and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, covered.
Cook, covered, until broth and rice are cooked well.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter or shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet; bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: beef and rice fiesta
directions: Brown beef in skillet, leaving meat in large chunks. Add onion and cook over medium heat until tender. Add water, soup, corn, salt and chili powder. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Add tomatoes and green peppers; cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Cook berries, 1 cup of sugar and 1/4 cup of water for 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water to thicken berries.
Cool.

title: mom's cherry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers, powdered sugar and margarine. Pack in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix Cool Whip, milk, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour onto crust. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: rolled chicken washington
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and stir in cream.
Add seasonings.
Cook and stir until mixture is very thick.
Add cheese and cook over low heat till melted.
Turn into pie plate, cover and chill 1 hour.
Cut mixture into 6 or 7 pieces, shape into short sticks.
Remove skin from chicken breasts. Place each piece, boned side up, between clear plastic wrap (overlap where meat is split).
Pound out from center with wood mallet to form cutlets not quite 1/4-inch thick.
Peel off wrap. Sprinkle with salt.
Place cheese stick on each piece, roll up chicken, tucking in sides as for jelly roll.
Press to seal well. Use toothpicks to hold together.
Dust rolls with flour, dip in egg, then in crumbs.
Cover and chill thoroughly - at least 1 hour or overnight.
An hour before serving, fry rolls in deep fat (375°) for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Bake in shallow baking dish at 325° for 30-35 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in glass bowl in order listed.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.
Sometimes I substitute Ranch salad dressing for the mayonnaise.

title: peanutty ice cream pie
directions: Combine the peanuts, butter and sugar; press onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 9 inch pie plate.
Cover and refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes, or until softened.

title: easy taco pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing edges together to form seal.
Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Fill with meat mixture and spread cheese over top.
Bake until cheese melts.
Add other ingredients.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid shortening or margarine (not oil), grease and flour 15 x 10-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
By hand, stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
In small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk. Boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until smooth.
Pour over bars.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: aunt charla's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and eggs; mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Measure milk and add vanilla to it.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes (approximately 1/4-inch thick).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cake surprise
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar, shortening, eggs, fruit cocktail (with juice) and cherry pie filling.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. After baking, sprinkle with desired amount of powdered sugar.

title: browned butter frosting
directions: Heat butter until golden brown.
Add powdered sugar and milk. Beat until smooth.

title: hamburger zucchini
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and salt.
Pour off fat.
Add tomatoes and cut up zucchini and simmer until tender.

title: herald of holiness rolls
directions: Mix the yeast and 1/4 cup water.
Add the sugar, eggs and additional water.
Then add to that mixture the oil, salt and flour.
Mix that all together.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add flour.
Roll out dough on floured surface. Thick dough makes softer cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux by browning 1/2 cup flour in 1/2 cup of well heated vegetable oil.
Lower heat and add water gradually.
Add onion, garlic, pepper and parsley then cook 30 minutes.
Add crabmeat.
This can be freshly cleaned crab or fresh or frozen. It is better to have claws and a few chunks of body meat in the gumbo.

title: apple cinnamon raisin muffin
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except the raisins.
Fold in raisins last.
Pour into Texas style muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to box.
Punch holes in hot cake.
Warm Eagle Brand milk and pour over cake.
Pour 1/2 can of cream of coconut over cake.
Sprinkle 1/2 can coconut over cake.
Freeze cake for one hour.
Cover with the Cool Whip and remaining coconut and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and peanut butter together.
Add egg; add flour with baking soda and vanilla.
Make small (1-inch) balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully; don't overbake.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mississippi yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add oil, buttermilk and soda; mix.
Then add flour.
Put mixture in large container. Chill.
Make into rolls as needed.
(Can be used for cinnamon rolls.)

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Mix the butter, sugar, egg white and vanilla.
Wrap dough around well dried cherries; dip in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill 10 minutes; place in covered container and refrigerate.
Makes 70 to 75 pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine and mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Add fruit cocktail, flour and soda.
Mix well and pour in baking pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Wrap bacon around chestnuts.
Put in a toothpick.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Mix sugar and ketchup and cook on stove for 10 minutes.
Put chestnuts in baking dish.
Pour Ketchup mixture over and bake 30 minutes at 350.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine oil and eggs; add rest of ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir over hot, not boiling, water until mixture thickens about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in marshmallows and fruits; fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Just before serving, fold in almonds.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with sour cream and lemon juice.
Add vanilla and lemon rind.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend together flour, salt and shortening.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Roll between waxed paper.
Makes 2 to 3 crusts.
May be frozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook Kraft macaroni and cheese; add can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes.

title: vegetarian stew
directions: In a large kettle, combine all ingredients except macaroni. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer until lentils are tender, about 45 minutes. Add macaroni and simmer until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Drain grease.
Add onion, oregano, garlic salt and chili powder.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes, water and salt. Bring to a boil.
Constantly skim off grease.
Lower temperature and continue cooking
until chili reaches desired thickness.
Add sugar to taste, if desired.

title: german chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, 1 egg and the margarine vigorously until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, 3 to 5 minutes.
Cover; let rest 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Press dough in bottom and up sides of pan.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl on medium speed.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar and the cocoa until fluffy.
Beat in 3 eggs, one at a time, and vanilla, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into crust.
Bake until crust is golden brown and center is set, about 25 minutes; cool.
Spread with Coconut-Pecan Topping (follows).
Refrigerate until chilled and firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and let set in refrigerator at least 24 hours before baking.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in bowl; pour into buttered casserole.
Pour melted butter on top; sprinkle nutmeg over top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In skillet, melt 1 tablespoon hot oil; cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove; pour off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling; return chicken to skillet. Cover; cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bob dust's seafood soup
directions: In a pot, add beef broth, water, onion soup mix and tomatoes. Bring to a boil.
Cut celery small.
We are using green beans or wax beans because of our diet.
You can add corn; add juice from the can and carrots, potatoes, onions and mushrooms (add juice from can).
Or you can use the mixed frozen vegetables to add to soup. If you use mixed frozen vegetables and you have to add more spices keep tasting to make sure its there is enough spices that are listed.
BRING TO A COMPLETE BOIL AND ADD ALL YOUR VEGETABLES. MAKE SURE THEY GET SOFT AND THEN TURN DOWN TO LOWER SETTING ON YOUR STOVE!
THEN ADD seafood.
If you can't find the seafood mixed then you can choose various seafood products to add to the mixture you make up your own mixture.
The more varieties of seafood the better the soup!
Add frog legs (optional).
Comes off the bone when cooking so beware of small bones if you have kids.
Let seafood cook 1/2 hour on lower heat setting and if it comes to a boil, turn down again.
Add your own salt and pepper if desired.
Then serve!

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter together.
Pour this mixture over 1 large box of Crispix.
Stir. In a large paper bag, pour in 1 box powdered sugar.
Put chocolate cereal mixture in bag also.
Close bag and shake until cereal is well covered.
Store in well-closed container.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and brown and white sugar.
Add 1 well beaten egg; add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to cream mixture.
Then add oats and mix well.
Shape into small balls (walnut-sized).
Then dip a glass into a small amount of sugar and mash each ball.
(May need to moisten the bottom of glass first.)
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili cheese spread
directions: With finest blade of food chopper, grind together cheese, cheese spread, onion and garlic.
Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly and stir until cheese is soft and pliable.
Form into long rolls and roll in chili powder. Wrap in waxed paper until ready for use.
Spread on crackers or use for sandwiches.
Keep cool until ready for use.

title: john y brown pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and blend well.
Stir in eggs, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Pie will wiggle when done; it sets as it cools. Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin burgers
directions: Mix and brown all ingredients together.
Let simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: raspberry-orange vinaigrette
directions: Dice onion and garlic.
Pour in raspberry puree, orange juice, ginger, soy sauce and balsamic vinegar.
Whisk in olive oil slowly.
Let sit for 1 hour.

title: "sherried" tuna chowder
directions: Put potatoes, onion and butter in pan and add enough water to cover.
Bring to boil and cook in rolling boil until they are soft and most of the water has cooked off.
Add rest of ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.

title: dill pickles(for 1 quart)
directions: Wash
cucumbers
good then mix water, vinegar, dill and salt. Put
cucumbers into this brine and cook cucumbers until they change
color.
Put
cucumbers
into
jars.
Add a small clove
of garlic
and 1 red pepper.
Reheat vinegar and water mixture
and pour
over cucumbers and seal.
Use 1/4 cup more water with pickle vinegar.

title: chocolate waffle cookies
directions: Melt together cocoa and margarine.
Mix eggs and sugar; add to melted mixture.
Add vanilla and flour to mixture.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Drain pineapple (save 1 cup of juice).
Heat oil in saucepan. Saute onions and green peppers for 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, vinegar, ginger and soy sauce.
Add pineapple juice.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture thickens.
Add the pineapple chunks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Beat in rest of ingredients. Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for an hour or until done. Stand for 10 minutes and invert pans.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Use hands to blend softened cream cheese, dates and mayonnaise.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Just before serving, spoon strawberry preserves over cheese ball.
Serve with Town House-style crackers.

title: favorite noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and cook noodles.
Saute onion and pepper in butter till tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives, and oregano. Add the browned beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Place half of the noodles into greased casserole pan.
Top with half of ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 c. of cheese.
Repeat.
Mix soup and water till smooth and pour over the noodles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°F for 30-35 min.
Spaghetti can be used instead of noodles.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil.
Add peas and allow water to return to a boil; cook for 20 minutes or until just tender. Drain and refresh under cold running water.
Drain well and set aside.
In another pot, bring 6 cups of water to a boil.
Add corn, carrots and celery.
Blanch for approximately 1 minute or until just tender.
Drain and refresh under cold water.
Drain well.

title: banana split brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth; spread over brownie. Top with fruits and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over brownie.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bananas, Egg Beaters and skim milk. Add flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a loaf pan that has been prepared with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted is dry.
If using a glass loaf pan, set the oven at 325°.

title: bread pudding cake
directions: Slice French bread into 1/2-inch round croutons.
In a large mixing bowl, combine milk, eggs and sugar.
Using a wire whisk, blend these 3 ingredients well.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg. Continue to blend until all ingredients are well mixed.
Oil a 10-inch cheesecake pan and cover bottom with parchment sheet. Place one layer of French bread croutons into the bottom of the pan, making sure there are no void spaces.
Sprinkle a small amount of pecans and raisins over this layer.
Ladle in 1/3 of the custard mixture.
Carefully press the custard into the croutons using the tips of your fingers. Continue this process until all croutons and custard are used up.

You may find that 1 to 2 cups of the custard mixture will remain once the pan has been filled. This is normal and you must continue to add custard, a little at a time, firmly pressing into the croutons until all has been used. This may take an hour or so.
The bread pudding is always best if allowed to sit in the refrigerator overnight before cooking. Preheat the oven to 375°.
Place the bread pudding pan into a larger pan filled with water.
Cook in this water bath approximately 1 1/2 hours. Allow to cool and serve with Praline Sabayon.

title: mother's oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oatmeal in hot water and then mix all ingredients as listed above, adding oatmeal last.	Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2 1/4
inch pan.

title: linda's southern vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Place the Swiss cheese on top of the chicken.
Mix together the cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can milk over low heat.
Pour mixture over the chicken and Swiss cheese.
Combine the melted margarine and the stuffing mix. Spoon mixture over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: veg-jitas
directions: Grill veggie burgers, corn, onions and peppers together. Transfer to a hot plate.
Cut the burgers into long strips and add grilled vegetables.
Place flour tortillas in aluminum foil to warm on grill (10 to 20 seconds).
Remove from grill and wrap up veggie mixture evenly in each tortilla.
Top each veg-jita with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine juice concentrates, pineapple juice, tea and maraschino cherries in large pitcher; mix well.
Chill, tightly covered, until serving time.
Pour into punch bowl.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until it is light and airy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, and put in pineapple (prefer to use crushed) and almonds. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add to batter alternately with juice.
Pour the batter into a greased, wax paper lined spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool in pan before removing. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or glaze it before serving.

title: five-can casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Place in casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mother's vanilla ice cream
directions: Note:
One gallon or 1 1/2 gallon freezer and 1 gallon crock.

title: cheese angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Line a 9 inch pie pan with pastry.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: sour brine pickles
directions: Makes about 12 quarts of pickles.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles.
Press perforations down to keep dough together.
Combine cream cheese, mushrooms and salt.
Mix well. Spread mixture equally over each rectangle of dough. Starting at long side, roll up rectangles, jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seams to seal. Slice logs into 1-inch pieces. Place seam down on a baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: For sauce, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir on medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Place half the sliced potatoes in a greased casserole.
Cover with half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes more or until potatoes are tender.

title: pecan loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, folding egg whites in last.
Pour into oiled loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast sausage venison
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into patties.

title: cherry cordial(wisniowka)
directions: Place cherries and 1/5 of the pits in a gallon jar.
Pour in vodka and alcohol.
Seal tightly and store at room temperature 1 to 3 months, shaking occasionally.
Strain through cotton-filled funnel, adding 3/4 to 1 cup simple syrup.
Age mixture 4 to 6 weeks before serving.
For a drier cordial, increase the amount of vodka to taste.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to directions on box.
Drain. Saute sausage and turkey.
In baking dish, spread spaghetti sauce in bottom of dish.
Add mostaccioli, pepper, sausage, turkey and shredded cheese.
Continue with sauce, cheese and meats in layers. Do this until all ingredients are used up.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes.

title: lea's beef stew
directions: Place stew meat in a covered casserole.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: norwegian fudge
directions: Cook sugar, water, cocoa and syrup to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool and knead into rolls.
Slice as needed. Nuts may be added.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir dry jello into cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and pecans and fold in Cool Whip.
If orange pineapple jello used, add Mandarin oranges along with the pineapple and nuts.
A few drops of yellow and red food coloring make a prettier orange.
Recipe doubles nicely.
(Best if made 3 to 4 hours ahead.)

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and add mayonnaise.
Chill and serve. (Serve on crackers, finger sandwiches or salad.)

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread in bottom of pie plate. Spread picante sauce over that. Layer with lettuce, tomatoes and onions; top with shredded cheese. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mary anne school boiled custard(a christmas tradition all my life)
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add to well beaten eggs; add salt, then milk.
Cook in double boiler over low heat.
Stir continuously until mixture coats wooden spoon.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Melt butter, add to potatoes, add beaten eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to potato mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and orange extract.
Put in 2 pie pans or 1 oblong pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
Soak in lime water (use glass or plastic container), 1 cup lime per gallon of water.
Soak 24 hours.
Wash thoroughly in cold water.
Soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Drain; mix the other ingredients in larger boiler.
Bring to a boil; pour over cucumbers.
Soak 12 hours.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the ingredients.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls; press together on baking sheet and bake.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dip mix together.
Spread on cooled crust (may not need entire mix).
Sprinkle broccoli, carrots, cauliflower and cheeses over mix.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: juice punch
directions: Place ingredients in punch bowl, stirring and letting juice defrost.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 2 daughters yum-yum
directions: Put through coarsest cutter of a meat grinder the dates, figs, raisins, pecans and ginger or orange peel.
If mixture is very stiff, add needed lemon juice.
Shape into balls or centers for dipping, or form into roll to be sliced.
Coat with confectioners sugar; wrap in foil.

title: potato salmon pie
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add butter and 1/3 to 1/2 cup evaporated milk to potatoes; stir well. Spread over bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan, building up a rim.
Drain salmon; break into pieces.
Spread half of salmon over crust.
Saute green onions in some butter until tender.
Blend flour, salt and dill weed in butter mixture.
Gradually add milk; cook until thickened.
Pour sauce over salmon.
Top with half of cheeses.
Layer rest of salmon, sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: summer chestnuts
directions: Wrap each chestnut in a piece of bacon and hold together with toothpicks.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix 1/2 cup chili sauce, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour mixture over chestnuts and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Cream together the butter and honey.
Blend in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Add bran and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix all dry ingredients and blend into banana mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; add sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Stir in 2/3 cup coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Shield eggs with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until set.

title: banana fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In heavy-gauge saucepan, melt 1/2 cup of Little Bits over low heat; remove from heat.
Stir in one cup La Creme whipped topping, eggs and sugar; mix well.

title: mustard pork loin
directions: Place roast on a rack in a roasting pan.
Salt and pepper roast, then spoon on mustard mixture (mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic cloves and Kitchen Bouquet mixed together. Bake
at 350° in a covered roaster approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until 170° internal temperature has been reached.
Remove roast; let cool for slicing, about 15 minutes or so.
Drain drippings.
Add water enough for gravy; thicken and serve while hot.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender.
Cool and dice.
Fry bacon. When crisp, remove and crumble over potatoes.
Stir flour into bacon fat and cook until lightly browned.
Stir in vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in onion and season.
Pour onion sauce over potatoes and bacon.
Toss.

title: non-shrinkable sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Measure 2 cups sugar (reserve 1/4 cup).
In a large bowl beat until frothy the egg yolks and boiling water.
Gradually add 1 3/4 cups sugar and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla and lemon extract.
Fold in only until blended.
Add egg whites (beaten stiff) with the 1/4 cup sugar reserved.
Fold whites into other ingredients and bake in ungreased angel cake pan 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Makes a very large cake.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water until you have 1/2 cup of juice.
Drain and cool.
Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs. Dissolve soda in cooled raisin juice.
Sift flour and spices together; add to creamed mixture alternately with raisin juice. Add vanilla.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gourmet golden squash
directions: Mash squash and stir in all ingredients.
Bake in ungreased casserole at 400° uncovered
for about 20 minutes.

title: peach glow salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Open ginger ale and allow to stand a few minutes until fizzing stops.
Add ginger ale to gelatin mixture.
Drain sliced peaches and arrange in bottom of 9 x 5-inch bread pan or individual molds.
Pour gelatin mixture over peaches and chill until set.
Unmold and serve on lettuce garnished with cream dressing.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked bean dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, vanilla, pineapple and bananas.
Add to dry ingredients until moist.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place
the beef
roast
into
a
crock-pot.
Drain
the mushrooms and add to the pot.
Mix the bouillon with the onion soup and pour over the roast.
Cook 10 to 12 hours on low or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients.
Add a dash of lemon juice. Onion may be added. Chill before serving.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold pudding mix in Cool Whip and then add remaining ingredients and then place in refrigerator.

title: chocolate-covered peanut butter balls
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and peanut butter.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in the top of a double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate mixture using toothpicks and a spoon. Makes 75.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the usual manner.
This recipe makes 2 loaf cakes (9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 3-inch) or 1 Bundt cake.
Pan(s) should be well-greased.
Pam spray works best.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: 2-step chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet. Then add can of soup and water. Cover and simmer until done. (Chicken should not be pink in color when thoroughly cooked.) Yummy!

title: mixer icing
directions: Beat until sugar is dissolved.

title: tarralli
directions: Start with eggs; add butter, sugar, milk, vanilla and baking powder.
Slowly add enough flour to make firm soft dough.
Flour hands.
Roll into 1/2-inch rings.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 375°.
Different flavors can be used instead of vanilla.

title: cabbs relish
directions: Coarsely chop all vegetables.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add to chopped vegetables and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Stir in orange peel and juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to low; stir in butter. Simmer 2 minutes until thick and syrupy.
Add carrots and stir to coat.
Transfer to dish and garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Melt over double boiler.
Dip covered cherries into chocolate mixture.

title: lemon chicken fettuccine with snow peas
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain grease.	Mix ingredients together with sausage
while hot.
Make into small balls.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Mix until wet and press in the bottom of a baking dish.

title: mimi's boston brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into 3 coffee cans.
Bake in a 400° or 450° oven for 40 minutes.
Turn coffee cans upside down for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together drained shrimp, a few tablespoons cocktail sauce and horseradish to taste.
Mix with cream cheese until creamy.

title: cheese potato
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed. Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake in oblong pan 45 to 50 minutes.

title: country fair cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg onto waxed paper. Combine raisins and water in small saucepan, bring to boil.
Remove from heat, cover.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend flour mixture until smooth.
Add cooled raisins with the liquid and oats.
Mix well. Cover bowl.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop cookies from rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until evenly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 94 cookies.

title: pecan pie(no syrup)
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Double ingredients will make 3 pies.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of batter into hot, greased, black skillet.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add remainder of batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tortierre(canadian pork pie)
directions: In a large, heavy pot, combine all ingredients, except crusts. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, draining fat off with spoon as mixture cooks.
Boil and mash the potatoes.
Add to pork mixture.
Stir until thoroughly combined.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1-quart hot water.
Add 1-quart cold water.
When gelatin starts to congeal, add other ingredients and pour into molds to chill.
Serve on lettuce with dressing.
Makes 18 portions.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; boil in salt water until soft.
Drain, saving a little water.
In olive oil, fry vegetables.
Cook meat in same pan.
Add all but paprika and mix well.
Breaking up eggplant, place in buttered dish.
Spread a little bread crumbs and paprika over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
The saved water is for making the consistency you want it.
This freezes well. Freeze before baking.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Set aside.
To the drippings add potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine flour and small amount of milk.
Add to the vegetables with the remaining milk. Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Garnish with bacon. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix in large bowl, then make into small bite size balls.
Bake in oven until golden brown on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Freezes well.
Makes 36 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the thawed broccoli, 2 beaten eggs, mayonnaise, mushroom soup and onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover mixture with grated cheese.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top of casserole.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding tarts
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Mix well. Beat in pudding mix.
Chill 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping. Place 2 banana slices on bottom of each crust.
Spoon equal portions of pudding mixture into each crust.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix together; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven until firm, about 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Cook spaghetti or egg noodles; drain and rinse.
