Saute mushrooms in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream, sherry, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Fold in chicken and cooked noodles. Turn mixture into a 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased baking dish (7 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Mix first 5 ingredients with a fork until crumbled. Place on top of apples.
Pour 1/4 cup of melted margarine on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to cover.
Strain broth real good. In a large Dutch oven melt margarine.
Saute medium onion and garlic clove.
Add flour, paprika, salt and Season-All seasoned salt.
Then add chicken broth, camino, sour cream, green chilies and chopped chicken.
Heat thoroughly.

title: aunt maurie's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup water and 1/2 can soup.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Spread remaining 1 1/2 cans soup over top.
Do not dilute. Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 350°.

title: cheddar filled beef roll
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into an 14 x 8 rectangle on foil or wax paper.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs, green pepper and water and spread over meat mixture.
Roll meat up, starting at narrow end.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice into 6 to 8 servings.
Lay flat in shallow pan or cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: choc-oat chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.

Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate chips. Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 9 to 10 minutes in 375° oven or press dough onto bottom ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta primavera freeh
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil in a large pot.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and stir in the fettuccine.
Cook until tender, but still firm and drain immediately.
Transfer the pasta to a large mixing bowl, add the olive oil and chopped purple onion and toss to combine.
Set aside to cool to room temperature.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Do not boil.
Add nuts to melted mixture and stir.
Pour this mixture over the top of the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip for fresh fruit
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve on tray with fruit (apples, strawberries, melon balls, grapes, kiwi dices and pineapple chunks).
Colored toothpicks help to pick fruit up. May also be served on top of molded fruit jello.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the order they are given. Pour into a 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce the heat to 350° and bake at 350° for 1 hour longer.

title: potato stroganoff casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups water and margarine.
Over medium-high heat, bring to a rolling boil; remove from heat.
Add milk and potato flakes; stir to desired consistency.
Set aside.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add gravy mix, 1/2 cup water and mushrooms; cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and dill weed.
Spoon into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken; pull meat off bones.
Spread chicken over bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread broccoli over chicken; drizzle soup over both.
Pour 1/2 can of milk over dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mama weldon's frosting
directions: Make coffee real strong.
String through cheesecloth.

title: hogie's bacon broil snack
directions: Half cook bacon in a microwave or pan-fry.
Lay out sliced bread on a cookie sheet.
Place one slice of cheese on each slice of bread.
Place sliced onion on cheese (to taste).
Place 2 to 4 slices of bacon on onion.
Place sheet under broiler until bacon is crisp (not burnt!).
Top with sour cream and chives to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Beat in peanut butter and milk until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into Oreo cookie crust. Sprinkle with grated chocolate, if desired.

title: charbroiled ruff grouse
directions: You will need a rich bed of hardwood coals (a gas grill is an alternative method of cooking as is the broiler in the range).

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon pieces in a Dutch oven until crisp; do not drain.

title: chunky chicken rice soup
directions: Cook celery and carrots in broth for 25 minutes before adding rest of ingredients.
Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in saucepan until browned.
Add broth, water, vegetables and seasonings. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in rice and parsley; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until ready to serve. Mmmmmm-good!
Always a hit.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Has crust on bottom, filling in middle and coconut on top.

title: rice and pork chops
directions: Roll chops in flour, then brown in oil.
Place chops in large casserole.
Place onion and pepper on top of each chop.
Top with rice and sprinkle with salt.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: susanna's california baked beans
directions: Drain kidney beans.
Mix everything, except cheese.
Mix well. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover. Bake 15 more minutes.

title: amish chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken in 2 or 3 quarts water.
I put in 3 bouillon cubes.
Add in onions and carrots.
Remove cooked chicken.
Add in potato, beans, peas, corn and margarine.
Get potatoes and carrots cooked, then add flour to milk and mix well.
Add chicken to soup, then pour in milk mixture.
Stir while cooking to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste!

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan
over
low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add	tomato	sauce and stir.
Sauce should be thick, but not
stiff.
Add
water	to desired consistency. Season with chili powder and cayenne pepper to taste.
Mix 1/4 cup sauce with chicken.
Fill
tortillas with chicken mixture. Roll up and place in rectangular casserole dish.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas
and
sprinkle
with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and chicken is heated throughout.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix oil, soy sauce, garlic powder and red pepper.
Add to noodles and refrigerate overnight, if possible.
(This marinates the flavor evenly.)
Add fresh vegetables before serving.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Place diced bread on bottom of an 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put cooked sausage over top of cheese.

title: easy beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; rinse and drain.
Brown ground beef with celery and onions; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato paste, water and tomatoes.
Add corn and seasoning.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Combine macaroni and meat sauce.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
If desired, sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian kifli cookies(hungarian cookies made by hand)
directions: In large bowl, blend butter and flour with hands until thoroughly mixed. Add sour cream and mix well. If dough is too sticky, add a little more flour. Using hands, roll dough into balls, using 1 tablespoon of batter for each. Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries and stir.
Cube cake into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour strawberry mixture over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill until set.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: nannie's egg bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, milk and melted fat.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just enough to moisten. Bake in 7 x 11 x 1 1/2 for 25 minutes at 300°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions, adding onion to cook also.
Drain vegetables and add celery, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine, then spread on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog and hamburger chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until desired thickness.
Chili freezes well.

title: not so hot, but great chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in shortening.
Add beef and brown. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder, kidney beans and stewed tomatoes.
Bring to a light boil over medium heat.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add tomato soup, cover pan and simmer at least one hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: chicken soup
directions: Clean chicken, removing fat.
Put in large stockpot.
Add celery, carrots, onion, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and water to cover chicken.
Put cover on pot.
Boil 2 to 3 hours, adding water as it evaporates.
Remove chicken to plate. Skim water to remove brown particles. Debone chicken. Cut some of the meat and return to pot. Add tortellini and rice (optional).
Add tomatoes (optional).
Other pastas may be added, if desired.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Mix soups, milk, chilies, chicken and onion; heat.
Place layer of tortillas in large buttered casserole; cover with part of the soup mixture.
Top with part of cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: virginia vincent's french dressing
directions: Combine in jar or bowl and shake or beat until well mixed.

title: aunt ophelia's banana bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix salt in flour.
Mix soda in buttermilk.
Mix flour and buttermilk alternately into the sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean! It's delicious!

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a rectangular baking pan.
Layer all ingredients in the given order, one at a time.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until the coconut is lightly browned. Cool for about 1 hour, then cut into small squares and refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries; refrigerate until slightly thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break up cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over cake. Gently mix to moisten cake.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar, pineapple juice and flavoring ahead of use and chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Melt butter.
Add to cake mix.
Stir (will be dry).
Spread fruit filling on bottom of oblong cake pan.
Spread cake mix with butter on top of fruit.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: jello coke salad
directions: Make jello, using juice from cherries and add water to make 2 cups.
Boil.
Add jello and let cool.
Then finish jello with 2 cups Coke.
Add all other ingredients, except Cool Whip. Refrigerate until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: de-licious pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Remove labels from milk cans, placing cans unopened into a large pot.
Cover cans with water and place on stove at medium heat.
Let boil 4 hours, adding water when needed to keep cans under water.
After 4 hours, remove cans from heat.
Let cool 15 minutes, then open cans by using an electric can opener, because cans are under pressure and contents can shoot out if a hand held opener is used.
Spoon out caramel into pie shell.
Cool completely; cover with Cool Whip.

title: prehistoric pudding(for kids)
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or in zipper style plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into each of 8 to 10 (7-ounce) cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Plant gummy dinosaurs or gummy worms, dinosaur-shaped cookies or other candy creatures into cups of dirt.
Use jelly beans for dinosaur eggs and chocolate covered raisins or malted milk balls for boulders.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat the broiler. Combine the butter, olive oil, garlic, shallots, chives, salt and pepper and paprika in a large bowl. Blend thoroughly. Toss the shrimp in the mixture until thoroughly coated. Broil the shrimp as close as possible to the flame for 2 minutes on each side. Serve immediately. Makes 4 portions. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Lightly coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray. In a large mixing bowl, combine soup, margarine, salt, pepper, onions and cheese. Mix well. Gently fold in the hash brown potatoes. Spread evenly into prepared casserole dish. Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate cookie pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt, baking powder and sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in cookies and nuts.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together and allow to set overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour, syrup, butter, salt and vanilla. Add pecans and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. The nuts will float to the top to form a firm crust that will brown nicely if baked slowly.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cut the kielbasa into diagonal slices. Place those and all other ingredients in a crock-pot. Cook on low at least 6 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until tender and drain well.
Add margarine and milk.
Crumble toast into the mixture; add other ingredients with salt and pepper to taste.
Add a dash of Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Grate a small amount of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix water, jello, sugar and lemon juice.
Let stand until cold and just starts to set.
Then whip jello mixture, milk and salt in a large bowl until stiff.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix good.
Best made day before.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Place in bowl and add the mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch and stir.
Chill.
Can use any kind of vegetable.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch pan the bread, then the ham and the cheese.
Beat eggs, add rest of ingredients, pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours in a pan of water. Serves 12.

title: glazed fruited chicken
directions: Drain fruit; set aside, reserving 2/3 cup liquid.
Stir reserved liquid into mayonnaise; stir constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Add stuffing; spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk over low heat.
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs and blend on low speed 30 seconds, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Keeps well for two days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil (1-inch) to 375°.
Mix cornmeal, salt, onion and baking soda.
Stir in buttermilk.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until brown, about 2 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put half of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Put in melted margarine and cut up chicken.
Mix celery soup and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Put in the rest of stuffing and add chicken broth.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk and flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and salt and pepper.
Pour potatoes into 2-quart casserole.
Cover potatoes with sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: oven turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except gravy mix.
Mix gravy, except use milk instead of water.
Add gravy to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients in dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Quick, easy dish; great with pork chops.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender for 30 seconds on blend. Sift last 3 ingredients together.
Combine both solutions and mix with spoon.
(Add walnuts, raisins or fruit, if you want.)
Bake in greased loaf pan for 45 minutes or until top is brown in a 350° oven.

title: french toast
directions: Blend ingredients.
Dip bread into liquid and fry.

title: crisco chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients at medium speed. Then add the eggs, milk and vanilla. Beat 2 more minutes. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bimbo's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter onto hot griddle into desired pancake size.
Flip over to brown other side.
You can check center to see if cooked all the way through.
Serve with butter and syrup of your choice.

title: pizza for one
directions: Brown ground beef, then add spices, sauce and cornstarch. Simmer for 8 minutes.
Add cheese and melt.
Serve with French bread cubes.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make a well in the center, place butter in well.
Add milk to well. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and add vanilla.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Chill.

title: rosti potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and drain immediately.
Cool and peel.
Shred into bowl.
Shred Swiss cheese into same bowl.
Add salt and pepper and mix well.
Fry in a hot buttered cast iron skillet or non-stick pan.
Brown on one side and turn.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cream filled cake
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Place cake on a serving plate and prepare the cake shell following the illustrated directions.
Tear the removed cake into small pieces and set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Be sure to mix cream cheese and coffee cream well before adding to cooled jello mixture.
You can add crushed pineapple, apples, grapes, cherries or nuts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and dip vegetables.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl with mixer, beat butter with sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs until blended.
Blend in flour and milk; stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised.
Using a wire whisk or rubber spatula, fold egg whites into lemon mixture.

title: easy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa in an 8-inch square pan.
Stir dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
Put vanilla, vinegar and oil (one in each hole).
Pour 1 cup water over mixture; stir well.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry punch(this recipe is inexpensive and delicious!)
directions: Combine and sweeten if needed.
Add 1 large bottle of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: my favorite meatballs
directions: Add enough milk to breadcrumbs to make them moist.
Combine all ingredients except sauce.
Mix well with hands.
Roll into balls.
Brown by frying until half done.
Add sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken liver dip
directions: Cut chicken livers in small pieces, saute in butter and garlic until cooked through.
Remove from heat, stir in Baccardi rum.
Cool.
Combine
mixture in blender with cream cheese, yogurt, salt, pepper, and basil.
Blend until smooth.
Chill several hours and serve with crackers.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut off tips of corn kernels into a large bowl; scrape milk and remaining pulp from cob with a paring knife.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil while stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and stir, then add 3 cups Quick Quaker oats.
Stir until all is coated.
Drop onto waxed or plastic paper by spoonfuls.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: john's hot chili
directions: Saute the first 6 ingredients in a preheated deep pot.
The aroma of the garlic will knock your socks off; that garlic, by the way, was left in chunks.
After the first 6 ingredients are slightly brown, add the remaining ingredients; cover and let simmer for at least 2 hours.
You'll love it.
Everyone else did, including the judges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter.
Mix vegetables with rice and spread in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Layer chicken pieces on rice.
Cover with sauce.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen before cooking.

title: asparagus ham rolls
directions: Place fish fillets in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and onion powder.
Lay 1 layer of fish fillets, then 1 layer of sliced tart apples.
Squeeze lemon juice over apples.
Make another layer as above.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pudding delight!
directions: Combine flour and butter until smooth.
Spread over a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: "brunch eggs"
directions: Place bacon in a single layer in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese, cover and chill. Break eggs over cheese, spacing evenly. Pour whipping cream over eggs and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Bake in a 425° preheated oven for 10 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, onion, peppers and salt stand 3 hours in salt water.
In large pan, put sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric; let all this come to a hard boil.
Put all this, cucumber, onions and peppers in this.
Let cook until tender, then can in jars and seal.
Take out of salt water, then put it in mixture to boil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until browned and tender.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese, and taco mix together until smooth for sauce.
Layer taco sauce, tomatoes, lettuce, and cheddar cheese.

title: honey raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Add the applesauce, egg and honey; stir until mixture is moistened.
Add raisins and nuts. Grease or spray muffin tins with nonstick cooking oil. Fill approximately 3/4 full. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, combine oats, brown sugar and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and crumble.
Stir together pie filling and cinnamon.
Divide mixture into 8 glasses and top with softened ice cream and crumbled oat mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening, 1/3 cup at a time.
Mix until consistency of peas, then add the second 1/3 cup and mix until crumbly.
Add 1/3 cup of milk very slowly until dough is smooth and damp to touch.
Roll out to fit pie pan and never, never re-roll pie crust dough.
You can freeze a double crust.
Put bottom crust fitted in pie pan, lay wax paper on top and then the top crust.
Slip the whole pie crust making into a gallon Ziploc freezer bag and freeze until ready to use.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth, add eggs, one at a time, mixing between each one.
Add the dry ingredients alternating with the sour cream.
Add the vanilla.
The batter is thick.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased 9x12-inch pan.
Cover with the pie filling.
Pour the rest of the batter over the pie filling.
Top with 1/4 cup of flour, 1/4 cup of sugar, 3 tablespoons of butter and mix into crumbles and sprinkle over the top of the cake and bake for 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork.
Pour into greased and floured large (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound to flatten chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook onion and celery in 3 tablespoons butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Add 3 tablespoons wine, crab meat and stuffing mix; toss.

title: broccoli recipe
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Drain.
Put butter in until melted, then add bread crumbs and onions.
Put in casserole dish. Mix the two soups together and put on top.
Take a knife and cut down through the broccoli mixture.
Heat in 350° oven until warm and blended.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast on aluminum foil; sprinkle with Lipton onion soup. Add cream of mushroom soup.
Wrap roast in foil; place in roasting pan.
Bake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kauai banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add bananas, vanilla and eggs. Separately sift all dry ingredients.
Add wet and dry ingredients. Mix lightly, do not overmix.
Pour mixture into 2 (1 pound) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hazel shafer's fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with sugar (1 cup) and allow to stand while you get dough ready.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put dough in the bottom of pan.
Pour fruit mixture over dough.
Pour water on top of fruit. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer until brown on top.

title: quick carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 (8 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in large bowl.
Add sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat until moistened and blended.
Stir in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Divide the batter between the 2 pans.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Lift loaves out of pans, turn down sides of foil and cool on rack.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: In large pot, bring to boil bay leaves and 3 to 4 quarts water.
Add lemon, onion and seasoning (or spice).
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add sausage.
Boil, covered for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Boil, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add corn.
Boil, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Cook just until all the shrimp turn completely pink.
(Do not overcook.)
Drain water.
Serve in the pot.

title: faye's favorite minute steak
directions: Cover both sides of minute steak with prepared mustard, then flour both sides.
Brown steak in oil on both sides.
Spread sliced onion over top of meat.
Mix soup and 1 cup water to make gravy.
Pour over browned meat and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Season as desired.

title: light n' fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip; then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit, if desired. Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill 3 hours.
Garnish, if desired.

title: burnt sugar cake with caramel frosting
directions: Burn 1/2 cup sugar in a steel pan to a deep brown; add water and shake well until all sugar is dissolved and set aside to cool. Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add egg yolks, that have been beaten.
Add milk and mix flour, which has been sifted 3 times with the baking powder and soda.
Add burnt sugar liquid and the beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in layers.
Quickly cover cake with Caramel Frosting.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve in a chafing dish with crackers.

title: roast pork with fennel
directions: Sprinkle generous amounts of garlic powder, salt, pepper and onion powder on all sides of meat and roll in fennel seeds.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Cut dough into pieces the size of walnuts.
Form into balls. Roll each in butter, then in sugar, cinnamon and nuts mixed.
Place 1 layer of balls in well greased deep 9-inch tube center pan so they barely touch.
Sprinkle with a few raisins.
Add another layer of balls, sprinkle more raisins in crevices pressing them in slightly.
Cover and let rise until light (45 min).
Bake, loosen from pan with spatula.
Invert pan so butter-sugar runs down over it.
To serve, break apart.
Bake at 375 for 35-40 minutes.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix.
Add to wet mixture.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pinch off 1-inch pieces.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and then add other ingredients alternately.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: spicy bread round
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients except bread. Place mixture in bread and replace lid.
Wrap in foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm with sliced, raw vegetables and toasted bread chunks.
Good with red, green and yellow bell peppers.

title: old-fashioned penuche
directions: Lightly grease sides of saucepan.
Add sugar and cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, with a wooden spoon, until sugar is dissolved.
You should not be able to feel sugar grains when you rub the spoon against the sides of the saucepan.
Remove from heat and with a damp towel, wipe sugar grains from the sides of the pan above the liquid level.
Return to fire; cook over medium heat without stirring, until candy thermometer reads 238° or soft ball when a little is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and without stirring, cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until fudge begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Stir in nuts and spread into lightly buttered pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine cheese and mashed potatoes.
Mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: pocket steak dinner
directions: Tear off enough foil to completely cover meat and vegetables. Place meat in center of foil on cookie sheet.
Spread onion soup mix on top.
Place chunks of vegetables on meat; dot with butter. Seal foil around entire thing to hold in meat juices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until vegetables are soft.
Gravy can be made from the meat juices.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Add milk to beaten egg and thoroughly combine.
Add to dry mixture.
Beat well.
Add apple slices.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden.
Serve warm with syrup.

title: jame's key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand or using a blender.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill at least 5 hours or overnight.

title: pork marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over pierced sirloin, pork chops and marinate all day in refrigerator.
Best when cooked on grill.

title: evelyn's bible cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey.
Add eggs, spices and vanilla. Add flour and milk alternating, beginning with and ending with flour.
Add raisins and figs.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cook meat loaf with all ingredients except tomatoes in oven until nearly done and browned on top, about 45 minutes, then add tomatoes and stir into drippings from meat loaf and finish cooking 30 more minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Build campfire.
Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Cook slowly all day over campfire.
If you've been trout fishing and have leftover corn, throw it in the pot, too.
(Do not throw red wigglers into the pot.)
Serve and enjoy around the campfire.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Fry bacon; drain.
Mix beef, bacon, onion, kidney beans, butter beans, pork and beans, catsup, brown sugar, green pepper, chili powder and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: greek style rockfish
directions: Put filets on greased sheet pan.
In saute pan, saute olive oil, garlic, peppers and onion.
Pour on top of filets.
Sprinkle oregano, then Feta cheese, then olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes per inch thickness.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramel and butter; add milk.
Pour over top of partially baked cake.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake batter over mixture, covering caramels mixture, chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for another 20 minutes.
Can serve with ice cream or Cool Whip on top.

title: make-ahead layered mexican casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, onion and seasonings, continually stirring.
Drain off excess grease.
Spread half of the meat mixture in a large casserole dish.
Top with tortillas. Combine beans with remaining meat mixture.
Spread over tortillas. Layer Monterey Jack cheese, then tomatoes, then Cheddar cheese. Top with soup.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in crock-pot. Cook on low if dressing is to be used later than 4 hours. If it is to be used within 4 hours, cook on high. You can add chicken breasts that have been cooked if you prefer. If you use the chicken, slice into small slices.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into the pie shell and top with another 3/4 cup of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: flank steak and spinach
directions: Mix spinach, cheese and sour cream. Spread mixture on one side of steak. Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. (2 carbs.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out dough.
Melt margarine and spread on dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; spread on dough and margarine.
Start at edge and roll; pinch sides together.
Slice in 1/2-inch cuts.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: stuffed chilies marinara
directions: Combine 3 cups cheese, bread crumbs, spices and egg.
Stuff chilies with mixture.
Arrange in shallow greased baking dish. Pour marinara sauce on top.
Sprinkle with remainder of cheese and chopped onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and cook for 1 hour at 250°.

title: shrimp and sausage gumbo
directions: In 2 quart saucepan, prepare rice as labeled.
Keep warm.

title: sweet noodle kugel
directions: Precook noodles.
Beat eggs and brown sugar until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Add nutmeg and lemon juice; continue to beat another minute.
Add noodles, melted margarine and raisins; stir until mixed well.
Do not beat.
Turn into margarine greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Dot with small pieces of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 (large servings).

title: darlene's dumplings
directions: Mix baking mix and milk and roll out thin on floured counter. Cut in strips with pizza cutter and drop in boiling broth, in which you've added your packages of Herb-Ox instant broth, seasoning chicken flavor mixes and salt.
Stir occasionally as you drop strips of dough in boiling water.
Boil about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Boil ingredients
over
medium heat.
Stir until thickened. Pour
into
pie shell.
Top with meringue made from egg whites, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: old fashioned dried apple stack cake
directions: Thoroughly cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg, molasses and buttermilk.
Blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly and add vanilla.
Chill dough until easily handled.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll each about 9-inch circles and place in greased 9-inch cake pans in 350° preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
When cool, spread layers with prepared dried apples.

title: gingered fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
In small jar, stir together remaining ingredients; pour over fruits, tossing to blend.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook
macaroni as
directed
on
package;
drain.
Heat cheese in skillet	until melted.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine.
Add crumbs and mix.
Press 1/2 of crumbs on bottom and sides of pan.
Mix Dream Whip and milk; beat well.
Add sugar and cheese.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture on crumbs.
Place strawberries on top of cheese, then add remaining cheese.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: illinois stroganoff
directions: Season stew meat with garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Put in crock-pot and add soups; mix well.
Cook on low for seven hours or on high for five hours.
Cook noodles and either serve separately or add to beef mixture.

title: peg's cherry cheese pie
directions: Melt butter slightly.
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and graham crackers.
Line pie plate with mixture.
Mix together cream cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Cream together well. Place into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until firm. Top with chilled pie filling once cooled.

title: peanut icebox pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with peanut butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust.
Garnish with chopped peanuts. Chill for several hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries with marshmallows.
Add the pineapple; mix well.
Add sugar; mix well.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Drain and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add Minute rice.
Mix together melted butter, Cheez Whiz, milk and mushroom soup.
Pour over rice and broccoli mixture.
Salt and
pepper to taste.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well while adding apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chocolate-cinnamon pudding
directions: In saucepan, heat 2 cups milk and the cinnamon until hot.
In another pan, mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in remaining 3/4 cup milk and add to hot milk.
Over medium-low heat, stir until boiling.
Over low heat, cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour into dishes.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 183 calories per serving.

title: peppe's coconut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and extract, then sour cream.
Add coconut.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Fold into batter.
Divide into four greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
You may easily measure to make 1, 2, 3 or 4 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and press on bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: harvard beet cake("beet haters love this recipe")
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil, butter, eggs and sugar.
Beat thoroughly.
Mix all dry ingredients very well in a separate bowl or sift ingredients.
Combine all ingredients, including remaining ingredients, in the large bowl and mix well.

title: indian love squash
directions: Scrub squash and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and stringy portion.
Pour ginger ale into large skillet.
Add squash, cut side down.
Cover pan and steam over medium heat 10 minutes. Arrange squash, cut side up, in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle each squash with salt and pepper.
To each half, add a teaspoon butter and sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, occasionally brushing with butter (both inside and outside of squash).
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven-made caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in a large, shallow sheet pan.
Put it in a very slow oven (250°) to keep warm and crisp.
Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in 2 quart heavy saucepan.
Place over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Continue to boil to the ball stage (248°), about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda; syrup will foam.
Return to oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Set; let cool.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: tasty spinach dip
directions: Squeeze out excess moisture of spinach.
Process until fine in food processor or blender.
Remove to a bowl.
Fold in the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well and add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
May be used as salad dressing.
Keeps well in refrigerator when stored in glass or Tupperware container.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add to creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 320° until done.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook together and cool the sugar, flour, pineapple juice, eggs, salt and lemon juice.

title: zucchini casserole a la marinara
directions: Wash and cut zucchini into 1/4 inch slices.
Cook onion in oil, then add the zucchini.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets. Cut most of top off.
Boil until done (stick with fork).
Drain water.
Cool.
Then peel skin.
Cut up however desired. Bring syrup to a boil.
Drop beets into syrup.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pack into jars and seal.

title: tuna melts
directions: Butter bun halves.
Spread with mixture (except cheese). Place slice of cheese on top.
Broil until cheese is melted. Makes 8 halves.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Boil new potatoes in their jackets until just tender.
Drain and add remaining ingredients to the pan.
Shake to coat the potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Let cool a little.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat again.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan greased lightly.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes. Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Combine baking powder and flour; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Mix butter or margarine and 1 cup sugar until light.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add potatoes and mix.
Mix milk with flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until dry but not stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff. Fold into mixture.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with
your favorite frosting.

title: fast and easy ice cream pie
directions: Slightly thaw ice cream.
Mix with undiluted fruit juice. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Refreeze; slice and serve.

title: scrabble(snack food)
directions: Melt together white chocolate and peanut butter in extra large pan. Mix together cereal, raisins and peanuts. Add to chocolate and peanut butter mixture and stir to coat. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Sprinkle ingredients in layers over top of ingredients already in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean. Good served with whipped topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, stir all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until all is moistened.
Turn into greased loaf pans (two 8 x 4-inches).
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: oatmeal ring-a-lings
directions: Mix together well shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in thoroughly flour, salt and oats.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a roll 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Coat each roll with chocolate shot.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least one hour.

title: brignole chicken
directions: Cut breasts in halves.
Remove skin and bones.
Slice into thin pieces and pound between waxed paper.
Dip chicken into mixture of salt, pepper, sage and flour.
Brown garlic; remove.
Saute chicken until brown; remove.
Add ham, mushrooms and onion to pan and cook until tender.
Return chicken to pan and add wine.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add butter and remove from heat.

title: turkey gravy
directions: In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water. In a large saucepan over medium heat, bring turkey broth and pan juices to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and continue heating until gravy is thickened. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: lemon snowflake cookies
directions: To make low-fat, use lite cake mix, lite Cool Whip and 2 egg whites.

title: cathy's layer dip
directions: Lay ingredients layered on a large platter.
First start with beans, next spread sour cream, guacamole, Cheddar and Jack cheese, tomatoes, olives and salt and pepper as much as you wish. Garnish top with green onions.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well; place in cut out center of pumpernickel bread.

title: ore dinner hot rolls(for a big family!)
directions: You will need a bread machine, if desired.

title: microwave cream of broccoli soup
directions: In 2-quart glass casserole, place broccoli, onion and butter; cover. Microwave on High 8 minutes or until broccoli is thawed or tender. Stir in seasonings and flour. Gradually add broth and milk, stirring until smooth. Cover and microwave 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally. Let stand a few minutes before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: company green beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine. Add to green beans and tomatoes. Add salt, garlic powder and black pepper. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: homemade reese's cup
directions: Melt margarine.
Work margarine, sugar and peanut butter together.
Roll into bite size balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and let cool on wax paper.
Use toothpicks to dip balls.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: In 1 cup water, soak barley overnight.
Drain.
Combine tomato sauce, water, mustard and vinegar.
Combine barley, ground turkey, onions, egg, garlic, pepper and 1/2 cup sauce.
Mix thoroughly and arrange in loaf pan.
Pour additional 1/2 cup sauce over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Not essential to soak barley but more tender.

title: pickles
directions: (Preparation Time:
20 Minutes; Cooking Time:
1 Hour 20 Minutes)

title: spicy beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chili con carne to beans.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add oil, coffee and milk.
Mix on medium for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes on medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° until cake pulls from side of pans (about 30 minutes).
Let cake cool 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: flower pot treat
directions: Use new washed flower pot (plastic or glass, not clay; it contains lead) with no holes in the bottom of the pot.
Alternate putting a layer about 1-inch thick cream cheese mixture, then Oreos until you reach the top.
End up with Oreos on the top so it looks like dirt.
Then top with gummy worms.
Mixture best if it sets for several hours in the refrigerator; overnight is even better.
Can use new washed digging spade to serve the flower pot cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and put into an uncooked pie shell.
Place half pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add olive oil.
Saute onion and garlic in same skillet.
Add rosemary, basil, black pepper and shrimp.
Cook until shrimp loses transparency (do not overcook). Add salt to taste.
Add wine and cook until oil and wine become slightly thickened.
Sprinkle parsley over.
Serve with fresh Parmesan cheese and lemon wedge to garnish.

title: famous cheese blintzes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks.
Trim crust off bread and roll slices flat with rolling pin.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and roll.
Pinch seam.
Dip in butter, then roll in sugar. Place in ungreased cookie sheet.
Freeze overnight (or until needed).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Great for making ahead and baking when wanted.

title: orange julius(a favorite with children.)
directions: Blend 30 seconds in blender. Serves 4.

title: swiss steak(stove top)
directions: Flour steak and brown in oil.
Remove from skillet and drain oil.
Pour 1 can tomatoes in skillet.
Place steak on top and pour remaining can of tomatoes on steak.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Blend 3/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons flour in shaker.
Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel and let stand about 10 minutes before slicing so they won't break apart too much.
Dice bacon; stir-fry until crisp.
To this add water, vinegar, salt, pepper, onion salt and 3/4 cup sugar.
Stir until blended.
Add water and flour mixture to mixture; stir until smooth.
Add to sliced potatoes, stirring with wooden spoon.
Serve hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
A little more milk may be added for heavy batter. Drop by spoonfuls the size of an egg in 400° oil. Drain and keep in hot oven.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; melt and pour over hash browns. Arrange hash browns in a casserole dish.
Let stand one hour. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Cover last 15 minutes.

title: payday bars
directions: Blend first three ingredients together well.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Spread marshmallows on top.
Turn off oven and return pan to oven, until marshmallows are melted.
Melt the 2 tablespoons oleo; add syrup, vanilla and peanut butter chips together.
Add peanuts and cereal; mix well and spread evenly over marshmallows.
Let set. Cut into bars.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Combine crescent rolls. Shape together like a pizza.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet.

title: cheesy chicken marsala
directions: Flatten chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper to 3/4 inch thickness. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place on jellyroll pan. Bake 15 minutes. turn chicken; bake until almost done, 10 minutes. Meanwhile, combine cheeses, tomatoes, parsley and oregano. Remove chicken from oven. Sprinkle each piece with one-fourth of mixture. Return to oven until cheese is melted and chicken is no longer pink in center; about 5 minutes. Transfer to platter. In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened. Whisk together broth and flour; pour into skillet. Bring to boil; cook, stirring occasionally until thickened, 4-5 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in butter until almost melted. Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle with additional parsley.

title: soft tacos(like chi-chi's)
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Mix Spanish rice as directed.
Spoon 2 tablespoons sauce in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set out a burrito.
Put 2 tablespoons rice, 2 tablespoons meat, cheese and salsa.
Roll side to side, moving filling in center.
Fold edges over like envelope. Place fold side down in pan.
Continue until all are placed in pan.
Cover with taco sauce and cheese.
Microwave for 3 minutes, or bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take out and serve topped with lettuce, onions and sour cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Add corn.
Stir in sour cream and eggs, then add muffin mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken over top; sprinkle onion soup mix and melted butter over chicken.

title: old-fashion gingerbread
directions: Mix and put into greased pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: company baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, saute meat, seasoning, onions and pepper until brown.
Drain.
Pour into heated crock-pot.
Add beans, barbecue sauce and syrup.
Mix; stir occasionally.
Heat for 1 hour.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Stew chicken breast in water until tender, save broth.
Cool chicken out of broth then take chicken off bone.
Butter a 9 x 18-inch casserole dish and place chicken, cut or torn in bite-size pieces, in dish.
Mix soups and sour cream in saucepan on warm or low heat.
Pour over chicken.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing crumbs.
Drizzle with butter and gently pour 1 cup broth over all. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Add 2 quarts milk.
This should fill freezer 2/3 full.
Freeze, using ice and rock salt.

title: cranbrosia salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; let sit awhile.
Drain oranges and pineapple and keep juices, then add 3/4 cup fruit juice and sprinkle gelatine over them.
Over heat, stir constantly and heat to dissolve good and add to fruit mix.
Whip together.
Add whipped cream.

title: lillian dodge's meat loaf
directions: Mix cereal and water; let stand 1 minute.
Combine with rest of ingredients except ketchup.
Put ketchup on top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon luscious
directions: Blend flour, butter and 2 tablespoons granulated sugar.
Pat into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: jackie's salsa
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients.
Serve with corn chips or with food. Good rolled in flour tortillas with grated cheese.

title: busy day salad
directions: Mix dry jello with the cottage cheese.
Then add pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Place walnuts in shallow pan (cookie sheet works well).
Heat in 350° oven 10 minutes; stir frequently.
Heat sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to 236° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well until mixture becomes creamy. May take 5 minutes or so.
Pour out onto cookie sheet and cool.

title: best christmas dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with plenty of broth.
Pour in large casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Stir over high heat until the sugar is dissolved: sugar, corn syrup, chocolate, salt and 1/2 cup cream.
Bring the ingredients to the soft ball stage, 234° over moderate heat.
Stir constantly. Add 1/2 cup cream.
Cook candy until it again reaches the soft ball stage, 234°.
Add 1/2 cup cream.
Cook to the firm ball stage, 244°.
Remove candy from heat to pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Do not scrape pan.
When candy is firm, about 3 hours later, invert onto a board and cut into squares.
Yields 1 pound.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole and cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
This freezes well if any is left over.

title: individual grilled dinner
directions: For each person, cut 2 rectangles of aluminum foil and lay cross ways.
In the center of the foil add potato, green pepper and onion.
Take ground beef.
Cube some Velveeta cheese.
Wrap ground beef around the cube of cheese to form a meatball.
This should make approximately 3 meatballs per individual.
Lay these on top of potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Top with 2 additional slices of Velveeta.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil
peppers
in
salted
water
for 5 minutes; drain. Scoop out
seeds	and fill with ingredients.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quik cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Add chips to dough mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: At least 2 hours before serving:
Arrange tomatoes in overlapping slices in serving dish.
Combine other ingredients and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Refrigerate until served.

title: old fashion cheesecake
directions: Blend cheeses.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls, pressing seams together.
Pour in batter.
Top with cinnamon and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
If using a glass pan, bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cake inside 5 to 7 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add cornstarch.
Add milk slowly while beating.
Add vanilla. Pour into two pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients but vanilla and nuts.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until soft ball forms.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan.
Cut squares when cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix in order given and freeze or chill overnight.

title: dipper's nuggets
directions: Mix eggs, water, salt, sesame seed and flour into a batter. Heat corn oil over medium heat in a heavy, sturdy, flat-bottomed 3-quart saucepan or deep fryer, filling utensil no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat, stirring until thick. Pour into a cooked pie crust, top with meringue.
Bake at 325° until brown to your desire.

title: broccoli chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice per instructions on box. Thaw broccoli.
Melt margarine in a pan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down in skillet with hot oil and sprinkle with seasonings.
Cook until golden brown on both sides. Remove to platter and keep warm.
Discard oil in skillet and add lemon juice and 1/4 cup water to skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring to loosen brown bits from bottom of skillet.
Pour drippings over chicken.
Garnish with fresh rosemary and lemon slices.

title: sour cream noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix with all ingredients and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake about one hour at 350°.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour boiling water over
chopped dates; add baking soda and let stand until cool. Cream shortening and sugar, add

beaten egg and vanilla; beat until well combined. Add date mixture, flour, salt and walnuts. Stir only until combined. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Let stand for 20 minutes. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of loaf comes out clean.

title: shrimp-crab casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: boiled salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil until thickened.
Put in jar and keep refrigerated.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: coneywich
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Stir in Manwich, relish, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Arrange frankfurters in sauce mixture.
I simmer for 10 minutes.
Toast buns lightly.
Put franks in buns; spoon mixture over them and top with shredded cheese.

title: broccoli and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Line bottom of pan with broccoli.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over broccoli and cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: melon colada
directions: Mix in blender with desired amount of ice for a slushy drink. Pour into tall glass.
Decorate with pineapple chunk and serve with a straw or two.

title: easy-breezy key lime pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
May add a few drops of green food coloring, if desired.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Double filling for larger size pie crust.
May decorate with kiwi slices.

title: sheath cake
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa, water and Crisco and heat to boiling point; pour over the dry ingredients. Mix in rest of ingredients. Grease and flour a fairly good sized oblong cake pan and pour in mix.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool; add chopped pears and pineapple.
Let jell in refrigerator until firm.
Top with Pear Salad Topping.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Dip into beaten egg, then into flour to which salt and pepper have been added.
Fry until golden brown in oil.

title: hot pineapple dish
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex bowl.
Crumble up crackers and sprinkle on top.
Pour on melted butter and bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Wash and drain cabbage wedges and carrot sticks.
Coarsely shred cabbage and grate carrots.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add grated carrots and stir-fry for 1 minute; add cabbage, onion, garlic powder, red pepper, salt and sugar.
Stir-fry for 3 additional minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir ingredients constantly.
Yields approximately 5 servings.

title: eddie's favorite lime jello salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add marshmallows, stirring until they are partially dissolved.
Let cool slightly.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mash cottage cheese and add to jello mixture, stirring with a fork.
Mix salad dressing with jello mixture until well dispersed.
Chill until firm in a cooled dish or jello mold.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Then eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to other mixture, alternately with the buttermilk and flavor.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together, add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients and the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
After baked and cooled, spread with frosting.

title: punch bowl dessert(serves approximately 20.)
directions: Place 1 layer of cake in punch bowl. Layer with 1 vanilla pudding already mixed, 1 banana, half of the crushed pineapple, 1 carton of the strawberries and 1 (8 ounce) frozen whipped topping. Repeat procedure. You may use chopped nuts and cherries on top. Keep refrigerated and serve.

title: crab souffle
directions: Drain and cut
crabmeat
into chunks.
Dice 6 slices of bread into 9
x
13-inch	buttered baking dish.
Combine crab, mayo, celery, green
pepper, onion and salt. Spread over bread in dish. Cube
remaining bread, place on top of crab mixture. Mix eggs and milk
together and pour all over in dish.
Cover and
refrigerate overnight.	Bake, uncovered, at 325°.
Remove from oven
and spoon undiluted soup over top.
Return to oven and	bake additional	hour.
During last 30 minutes, sprinkle cheese on top.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: corn bread
directions: Spray pan with Pam and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry-o cream pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Let set until firm in refrigerator.
Pour cherry pie filling over top.
Serve when chilled.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake mix until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Lay can of apple pie filling over crumbs.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix sour cream and egg and drizzle over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and vanilla; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour	into pie crust. Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan or one deep enough for all ingredients. Sprinkle dry rice over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over dry rice.
Mix chicken soup and liquids together.
Pour over other ingredients in pan (will be runny).
Brush chicken pieces (approximately 8 pieces) with margarine and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not double recipe.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind fruit
together.	Add
sugar
and let stand.
Mix jello. When it begins to set, add the fruit mixture and nuts. Chill until firm.
Fills	9
x
13-inch
pan
or a large round mold.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Mix crushed crackers and sugar and butter; press into a rectangle dish for 10 to 15 minutes and cool.
Scald milk and add sugar and beaten yolks.
Cook until spoon is coated.
Remove from fire and add gelatin softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Cool and add whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust and sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.

title: edwards' seafood chowder(flavored with hickory smoked bacon!)
directions: Cook bacon; drain and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute celery and onion in bacon drippings; add potatoes, 2 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add bacon and fish and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except ground pepper and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes. Do not boil.
Garnish with pepper and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In a large mixing bowl combine milk and All-Bran until softened.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spray muffin tin with Pam. Fill cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 12 large muffins or 48 mini muffins.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in bowl until moist; do not beat.
Put in a greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in double boiler. Add eggs, milk and vinegar. Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick. Add butter; cool. May be stored in refrigerator for 1 month. Makes 1 quart.

title: basil vegetables
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until onion is tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, zucchini and basil.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered until zucchini is crisp and tender, about 3 minutes longer.
Stir in cheese.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed and drain.
Rinse to cool.
When pasta is cooked add all other ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: healthy honeys
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey, dry milk and Wheat Chex crumbs. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll into Rice Chex crumbs.
Press 1 Rice Chex crumb into each ball. Cover.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 30.

title: broken glass jello salad
directions: Mix 3 (or 4) packages of colored Jell-O with boiling and cold water.
Set each color of Jell-O in shallow pans until firm.

title: sweet corn relish
directions: Add all ingredients and mix together good.
Cook 20 minutes in open jars.
Seal at once.
Yields 8 pints.

title: german strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for one hour, or until cake tester is clean.

title: roast
directions: Put roast or steak in crock pot. Pour soup over meat. Cover and cook 3 to 4 hours. Will make it's on gravy.

title: chocolate chip cookies(for diabetics)
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients.
Cream butter.
Add sugar substitute, vanilla and egg, blending well.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for eight to ten minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries and remove stems.
Put cranberries and water in large pot.
Cook over medium heat until cranberries break open. Add sugar slowly and bring to a slow boil.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove pot from heat.
Let stand until cranberries are cool.

title: lobster scramble
directions: Steam lobster pieces.
Set aside.
Toss scallions and mushrooms in butter, cooking in skillet until starting to get tender.
Add seasonings and lobster until everything is hot. Serve hot!!!

title: english toffee(candy)
directions: Cook sugar, butter and water to hard crack stage.
Put chopped nuts on bottom of a pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: honey pepper chicken
directions: Mix honey, pepper and ginger together.
Coat chicken thoroughly with mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, peanut butter, eggs, shortening and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients. Cut up broccoli, cauliflower and onions and add to the mixture.

title: lamb (irish) stew
directions: Add lamb chops to pot; cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Skim fat off top.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Sprinkle parsley, couple dashes of Gravy Master and 1/2 package of spaghetti sauce. Simmer covered 1 1/2 hours.
Boil potatoes until tender on side. Drain.
Add potatoes and McCormick gravy mix.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven the 375. In a small bowl, mix together cheese soup and milk. In a medium bowl, combine chicken, salsa, chilies, and only 2 tsp. of the soup-milk mixture. Spread about 1/3 cup chicken mixture on each tortilla, and roll up. Place tortillas in a lightly greased 3 qt. baking dish and spread remaining soup-milk mix on top. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve with sour cream and black olives, if you wish. Makes 8 servings.

title: holiday salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Then add lime jello and lemon jello.
Allow mixture to cool.
Next, beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Add cherries.
Add pecans. Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli into a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together the sour cream, soup, celery and pimento.
Pour over broccoli and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: spanish beans
directions: Cook the beans according to the package directions.
Add the remaining ingredients and turn into a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: busy-night breakfast bake
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain. Layer potatoes, sausage and cheese in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: easy pineapple buns
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, margarine and
cinnamon
in a bowl. Mix well. Spoon mixture evenly into 10
greased cups of a
cup muffin pan. Place 1 biscuit in each
cup.
Bake
at 425° about 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert
pan on plate. Serve warm.

title: baby food cake
directions: Add 1 cup chopped nuts (pecans). Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twin nut wonders cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour and almonds.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form tablespoons of dough into 2-inch fingers by rolling lightly on pastry cloth.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: california casserole
directions: In large skillet, combine beef, garlic, salt, pepper, sugar, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Bring to boil; break up meat and cook on simmer for 15 minutes.

title: easy pineapple chicken
directions: Bring broth to a boil; add chicken cubes.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add undrained pineapples,
carrot slices, red and green peppers, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir cornstarch into soy sauce until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: real good slaw
directions: Shred amount of cabbage needed.
Add dressing mix (amount desired).
Stir well.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: chalupas
directions: Saute onions in oil until clear.
Add garlic, tomatoes and chilies; cook slowly 2 hours.
Add cheese.
When melted and real hot, stir in whipping cream. Serve on tortillas that have been fried a short time in oil or cooked over steam.
May also use sauce as dip.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Clean and boil shrimp.
Saute onion in margarine until tender. Make a sauce by adding soup, lemon juice and seasonings.
Fold rice and shrimp into sauce.
Fold in sour cream and pour into 1-quart buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Heat in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces and place in bottom of dish. Mix strawberries and dry jello together.
Pour over cake.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Pour over strawberries. Top with whipped topping and garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: chili in the pressure cooker
directions: Brown meat and onions and peppers in cooking oil. Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans. Cover. Set control at 15 pounds pressure and cook for 10 minutes after it starts jiggling.
Cool cooker. Add kidney beans and simmer for a few minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix 2 cups of dressing with remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased casserole and top with remaining 1/2 cup of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls in slow cooker
directions: Drop cabbage into a large kettle of boiling water and cook 4 to 8 minutes or until outer leaves come off easily.
Drain and cool. (Cabbage can also be cooked by placing in a large plastic bag and putting in microwave on High for about 5 minutes.)
Remove outer leaves (8 to 10).
Shave a little off the stem area of leaf to make them easier to roll.

title: no-cook easy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and cocoa.
Melt butter and add to the dry ingredients along with vanilla.
Mix with wooden spoon. Put mixture into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
When chilled, cut into squares.

title: reese peanut balls
directions: Cream with hands and roll into small balls, size of large marbles.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in melted chocolate mixture.
Put on waxed paper to drain.
Makes about 200 average size balls.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool and pour over vegetables.

title: sausage peanut pilaf
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Add celery and onion; cook 3 minutes.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add cooked rice, soup and pepper to sausage mixture.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve topped with sliced olives.

title: gobble-de-goop
directions: Douse gobbler with seasonings and lay to rest in slow cooker (or deep, deep casserole).
Mix sour cream with flour, soup, mushrooms and soda pop.
Pour all over everything.
Cover pot and cook on low (or bake at low temperature) from breakfast until dinner.

title: mushroom potato soup
directions: In a kettle, melt 3 tablespoons of the butter; add leeks and carrots.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in water, dill, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add potatoes.
Simmer, covered, until potatoes are just tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Rinse, pat dry and slice fresh mushrooms or drained canned mushrooms.
In a large skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Add mushrooms; saute about 5 minutes.
Combine milk with flour; stir in soup along with mushrooms.
Cook and stir until lightly thickened. Makes about 14 cups.

title: clams oregano
directions: Saute the chopped onion and pepper in the butter until soft. Add rest of ingredients, including clams with their juice; mix well.
Spread in shallow oven-proof dish (a quiche dish or pie plate works well).
Top with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers or Fritos.

title: aunt emily's sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and whip to a cream. Dissolve soda in sour cream and add to sugar mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture with vanilla.
May need to add more flour to make a stiff dough to roll and cut out cookies. Good plain or with icing.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: country turkey noodle soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine all ingredients, except turkey and noodles.
Cover; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Add turkey and noodles.
Heat through.
Makes 7 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
(If no orange juice is available, use water, not milk as milk makes bread heavy.) Cook in a glass loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or when an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: annie's spiced tea mix(makes 2 quarts mix)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put 2 to 3 heaping teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
