(Either candies or sugar may be omitted if too sweet for individual taste.)

title: mile a minute cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift again with the baking powder, salt and spices.
Combine all ingredients in the order given, adding the chopped dates and chopped nuts last.
Beat all together 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan in a moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Ice with Peanut Butter Icing.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Pour all but 1/4 cup bacon grease from skillet.
Add celery, onion, salt and flour; simmer, stirring constantly.
Add sugar, vinegar, pepper and water and bring to a boil.
Toss bacon and potatoes together in a 3 quart baking dish. Pour hot mixture over potatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat.
Drain all grease off.
Add all ingredients to meat.
Add rice last and stir thoroughly.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix and blend until creamy the rest of the ingredients and then add flour mixture.
Put cake circle back onto cupcake and ice with either vanilla or chocolate icing.

title: fruit punch
directions: Turn juices into a 6-quart mixing bowl or pan.
Stir in ice water and ginger ale.
Serve cold.
Yields 10 servings.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Spray an 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel.
Mix Jell-O and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows; microwave 1 minute or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
Stir mixture until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
(Creamy layer with float to top.)
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set. Loosen edges with a knife.
Starting at one edge, roll up tightly. With seam side down, cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.
Serves 8.

title: peach pork picante
directions: Coat pork cubes with taco seasoning. Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook to brown, stirring occasionally.
Add salsa and preserves to pan. Lower heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with hot rice and mixed bean salad.
Serves four.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix in bowl; pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.
May add 1 1/2 cups coconut (optional).

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until mushrooms collapse and give up their liquid.
Uncover and saute until onions are lightly browned.
Stir barley into mixture; saute 2 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling over high heat, then reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for about 15 minutes or until barley is tender.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mrs. smith's oven cooked chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Roll chicken in ingredients.
Bake at 310° to 325° in pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion and green pepper (diced) in oil until softened. Add carrot and cabbage.
Add in tomato juice and water.
Let come to a boil.
Add bouillon cube, Miso, soy sauce and spices.
Stir until cube and Miso dissolve.
Cover and let cook on medium heat until carrots are done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease tube pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: very good fruit cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oleo and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: biscuits
directions: Beat sour cream and Seven-Up with wire beater.
Add sweetener and biscuit mix.
Stir this well with spoon.
Use dry biscuit mix to roll out biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in 1 cup water.
Add other ingredients and cook over slow heat until pepper and onion are tender and gravy is thickened.

title: chicken asparagus melt
directions: Place each chicken breast half between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Lightly pound chicken with flat side of meat mallet or rolling pin until 1/4-inch thick.

title: cold choco-coffee drink
directions: Add 7 cups water to a cooking pot.
Add 10 tablespoons of coffee.
Bring to a boil.
Slightly reduce heat and boil about 20 minutes.
Let coffee cool.
Strain coffee through a tea strainer into a 2-quart pitcher.
Rinse out remaining coffee grinds from pot.
Strain coffee again back into the pot.
Add sugar and chocolate syrup.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and pour back into pitcher.
Add milk to blender of Choco-coffee mixture and ice cubes; blend until ice is crushed.
Enjoy!

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add cocoa or chocolate, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients with hand mixer until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares and enjoy with a cold glass or milk or a bowl of ice cream.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix pudding mix with cake mix; add all dry ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil without stirring, to 234° (soft-ball stage) or until syrup, when dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
(Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of saucepan.)
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (lukewarm).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares, about 3 dozen candies.

title: patriotic cake
directions: Set out ice cream to soften.
Cut butter into dry muffin mix. Place in casserole dish; do not press.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 10 minutes until mix begins to brown.
Remove and let cool.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture in a 9-inch pie plate.
Add softened ice cream and top with crumb mixture. Freeze.
Top with blueberries from muffin mix and sliced strawberries.
Let pie sit about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix until thickened. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate. Decorate top of pie with shavings of chocolate.

title: little pizzas
directions: Split muffins or bagels.
Toast lightly.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon olive oil on each (optional).
On each 1/2, spread 2 to 3 tablespoons tomato sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then top with Parmesan cheese.
Top with salt, pepper, pepperoni, cooked sausage or whatever is your favorite.
Bake in a 450° oven until cheese melts.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in pineapple, half the walnuts, green pepper, onions and salt. Wrap in plastic wrap and place in bowl.
Chill. Remove cheese ball wrapped in plastic and shape into a ball. Coat the outside with chopped walnuts.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but still shiny.
Add sugar gradually, beating in well.
Mix in almond extract, coconut and corn flakes.

title: delicious cinnamon layered twists
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add 2 cups flour.
Beat well; add softened yeast and eggs.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough; turn out on lightly floured board and knead until satiny.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled. Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll out to sheet about 5 inches wide and 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with oleo and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon which have been mixed together.
Fold over in thirds.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Repeat, spreading with oleo and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Fold again in thirds. Cut into thirds.
Cut into strips 3/4-inch wide by 3 inches long. Twist dough strips by turning ends in opposite directions.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: ginger cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add molasses and eggs.
Add flour with spices.
Put soda in cup; pour hot water and stir.
Put into cake mixture and bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry whipped cream
directions: Drain 1/2 package of frozen sliced strawberries; set remainder aside for garnish.
Puree drained frozen or fresh strawberries in blender or sieve to equal 1/4 cup puree.
Beat cream with confectioners sugar until stiff; fold in strawberry puree.
Makes about 1 cup of topping.

title: budget hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell peppers in butter. Cook potatoes and carrots until almost tender; add to hamburger along with the seasonings. Mix flour with water and add to thicken. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes, adding more water as needed. Serves 4.

title: mrs. lessie justice's date nut loaf bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour water over the nuts and dates on which soda has been sprinkled.
Let cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, flour, dates and nuts to the mixture.
Bake in small loaf pan about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon; pour off all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add onion.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove from heat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Wash all vegetables.
Boil water until it starts bubbling. Pour macaroni out of box into boiling water.
While noodles are cooking, boil your eggs.
Let macaroni cook 15 minutes, or until desired tenderness.
Drain macaroni, peel eggs, cut eggs into macaroni, then add mayonnaise, diced green pepper, onion and tuna. Add to the macaroni, then add a pinch of salt and pepper.
Mix together and refrigerate and serve cool.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes on high speed of electric mixer.
Add gradually sugar, baking powder, pumpkin, flour and cinnamon.
Pour into long baking pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto another piece of wax paper, sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove top piece of wax paper and roll the cake jelly roll fashion.
Cool in the refrigerator.
When cake is completely cooled, unroll and spread the inside with filling.

title: chocolate shake
directions: In blender, combine milk, pudding mix and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice, cover and let stand 3 minutes to thicken.

title: brownie pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and cocoa in pan over medium heat.
Stir until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350 oven till set.
Serve warm.
Store in air tight container.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Soften cream cheese and add shredded crab, ginger, garlic and scallions.
Mix thoroughly.
Separate and lay out wonton wrappers on flat surface.
Drop one small spoonful of mixture in middle of wrapper. Dip index finger in milk and moisten surface of two sides of wrapper.
Fold wrapper into triangle and lift two points and twist together with a dab of milk so they will stick together. Drop in hot oil and cook for approximately 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with sweet and sour sauce or hot mustard sauce.

title: tropical delight
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 3/4 cups hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate to congeal.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 1 hour in tube pan.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; add onions, celery and pepper until tender.
Add pimento, mushrooms and chicken broth.
Put rice in large casserole dish and pour mixture over rice.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until rice is tender.

title: simple baked cheesecake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Pour into ready made graham cracker crust (or into a spring-form pan with a prebaked crust).
Bake at 325° until center is set, about 1 hour.
Cool.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg all together; pour over French bread in baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans over top. Cut butter in chunks and place on top. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until butter and sugar melt well.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: May use any type of pizza crust.
Put sauce on crust, then layer ingredients any way you prefer.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 250° to 300° until crust is done and toppings melt together.

title: pizza pinwheels(yield: 16 pinwheels)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine together. Add sugar, beating slowly. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating slowly after each addition. Add a small amount of flour at a time. Add vanilla and beat well. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: springtime punch
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes; remove from the heat.
Stir in the lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, using eggs and oil according to package directions.
Pour half the mix into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cream sherry cake
directions: Place cake mix and pudding in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil and sherry.
Start mixer on low speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Then turn mixer to high speed for five minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan or Bundt pan.
If you use tube pan, bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
If you use Bundt pan, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together until onion is cooked, but not brown.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream together.
In buttered, 3-quart casserole dish, make layer of noodles, cheese mixture and tomato sauce. Repeat layers, ending with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Combine egg, applesauce, honey, oil and apple juice.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Fill 12 greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: potato and pea casserole
directions: Make white sauce by combining margarine, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over peas and potatoes in casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Add cheese for topping.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese-onion spoonbread
directions: Cook onion in 1 teaspoon butter until tender.
Combine egg and milk in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Add onion and half of the cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and poppy seed over the top.
Drizzle melted 2 tablespoons of butter over top.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix with milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Crush cookies in food processor.
Begin with a layer of crushed cookies, add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers and end up with crushed cookies on top.

title: smoked salmon canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a sheet of the defrosted puff pastry into 3 equal pieces, lengthwise, and put them onto a parchment-lined (or foil-lined) cookie sheet.
Brush the surface of the puff pastry with the egg and milk mixture, and bake according to package instructions.
Leave to cool.
When cool, slice each piece of puff pastry, now risen, in half the long way with a serrated knife.
Spread three

halves with the creme fraiche (or sour cream or soft, room-temperature cream cheese) and top with smoked salmon and a sprinkling of chives or scallions. Cover with the other half of the "sandwich" and cut each of the three long "sandwiches" into four or five pieces.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat the cake mix, flour, oil and eggs together in mixer for 4 minutes.
Dissolve the jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Let cool. Add the strawberries to the jello.
Add to the first mixture.
Beat 4 minutes.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brunch
directions: Prepare ahead 4 slices bread crumbled.
Place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon meat over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper together and pour over bread and meat mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, cream cheese, condensed milk and lime juice in food processor or blender; process until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool at room temperature for about 10 minutes, then refrigerate until chilled.
Garnish with whipped cream and lime zest or cartwheels before serving.
Yields 1 pie.

title: chili cheese burgers
directions: Combine sour cream, chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside.
Mix beef, chilies, cheese, 1 t salt, cumin and pepper. Shape into 4 patties.
Broil 8-10 minutes on each side. Top each patty with 2 T sour cream.

title: carol ann's seven layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Layer mushrooms, onion, bacon, cheese and peas.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread on top, being careful to seal the edges.
Garnish with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: little chicken pies
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, shredded cheese, vegetables, soup and onion; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 triangles; press to seal.
Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture on one half of rectangle.
Bring remaining half of rectangle over meat mixture and press edges with fork to seal.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Serve as a dip with raw vegetables.

title: creole rub
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container. Sprinkle on chicken or beef before grilling or baking.

title: date balls
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, place dates, butter and sugar. Stir constantly until melted.
Slowly add slightly beaten eggs; cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Stir.
Roll in balls, then roll in coconut until covered.
Cover and place in icebox to chill.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Melt margarine.
Meanwhile, on wax paper, combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken in margarine and roll in crumbs to coat.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Roll into ball; roll in nuts.

title: oven steamed rice
directions: Combine rice, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13 inch pan, ungreased. Dot the top with butter and pour boiling water over top.
Stir until butter is melted.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not peek or stir.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: banana nut bread with currants
directions: Puree the bananas in food processor.
Add the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla and process just until blended.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and nutmeg.
Mix until combined.
Add nuts and currants.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: leche flan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Caramelize 3 tablespoons white sugar in a baking dish.
Caramel must cover surface of dish.
Use baking dish that is round, about 4-inches deep and 9-inch width.
Gently beat egg yolks with one whole egg.
Add condensed milk; beat gently.
Add vanilla extract.
Butter a cooled baking dish.
Pour mixture into the caramelized dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour over a water bath.
Leche Flan is cooked when toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in chile powder.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients starting with lettuce on bottom in a long pan.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread on top.
Cover with foil and let stand 10 to 12 hours.
Whe ready to serve, grate some Cheddar cheese on top and garnish with tomatoes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Blend in Cool Whip.

title: easy company cabbage
directions: Clean and shred cabbage.
Saute onion in butter in a pot.
Add cabbage and milk very slowly until cabbage is soft and milk is thickened.
Season with salt and pepper; put in a shallow oven-proof dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and put under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: beef steak - potato scallop
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; coat with flour.
Melt shortening in skillet; brown meat.
Add onion; cook and stir until onion is tender.

title: fudge(homemade)
directions: Heat to a boil all but the vanilla, nuts and butter.
Make it a rolling type boil for about 30 minutes.
Test at 15 or 20 minutes.
Do not stir as it makes it too sugary, just clean sides of boiling syrup with a spoon.

title: judy's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, then fruit.
Pour in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve room temperature with Cool Whip.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place ingredients in jar in order listed.
Keep in refrigerator.
Two or 3 recipes needed to fill 1 gallon jar.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: For sauce, in a 2-quart saucepan cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar and 1 teaspoon oregano, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat, discard bay leaf.

title: soupeior italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
In pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at oven at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bahian shrimp muqueca(muqueca de camarao)
directions: Heat the oil in a medium-sized pot and stir-fry the onion until golden brown.
Add the garlic and prawns.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes. Add the salt, lemon juice, tomatoes, parsley, pepper, cayenne and coconut milk.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with Brazilian Rice with coconut milk.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: different potato salad
directions: Layer cooked potatoes in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with wine.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake in two 9-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and split cakes into halves.
Cook 7-Up, cornstarch, sugar and food coloring until thick, like pudding.
Slice strawberries and pour mixture over berries; cool. Put Cool Whip and mixture over cake.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix soda and vinegar, set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa in a large bowl. Add the egg and sugar mixture to the paste.
Add the buttermilk along with the salt, sifted cake flour and vanilla.
Fold in vinegar and soda.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes after cooling.

title: turnip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in small skillet; add garlic and almonds.
Cook and stir over medium heat until almonds are lightly toasted.
Drain; cool on paper towels.
Discard garlic. Chop almonds very fine; set aside.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour, then stir in eggs, flavoring, milk and vinegar and put butter in last.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until golden brown.

title: ham pie
directions: Boil ham and water slowly in medium boiler for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add chopped eggs, pepper and flour.
Pour into pie pan and top with pie crust.
Dot top of crust with butter.
Bake at 450° (232°C) until pie crust is brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts; shred meat.
Cook tamales according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole(s) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute seasonings in butter.
Add 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir well.
Add crawfish.
Cook on low, stirring often for about 15 minutes.
Add cheese, half and half, salt and pepper.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Add cooked noodles; sprinkle with Parmesan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green pepper, onion, salt and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and garlic; cook, stirring constantly, until rice is tender, about 1 minute.
Add broth, wine, paprika and saffron; bring to boil. Stir in tomatoes, breaking up with spoon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in olives.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: star dust pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour pan. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Beat shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and lemon extract.
Start with flour and end with flour. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes for loaf pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cut thin for serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
In a large bowl, combine margarine, sugars, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Cream on high speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Turn to low speed and add flour mixture.
Blend for 1 minute, scraping sides of bowl as necessary. Form 1-inch dough ball between palms.
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Rinse beef with hot water.
Add other ingredients and place in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry-raspberry drink
directions: In a blender combine yogurt and cranberry juice.
Add strawberries, raspberries and sugar.
Cover and process until blended.

title: guava ginger fruit punch
directions: Peel and chop ginger.
Boil with 1/2 cup water until a strong ginger flavor.
Cool and strain through cloth; squeeze ginger. Boil 1 cup water with sugar until dissolved.
Add tea and ginger water.
Cut and press guavas through sieve.
Add to cooled ginger tea mixture and combine with all other juices.
Serve over ice.

title: pizza bites surprise
directions: In a frying pan, combine garlic, green pepper and butter. Cook slowly until soft.
Add tomato sauce; heat.
Add chicken and oregano.
Separate biscuit dough.
Halve each slice.
Place on a greased baking dish.
Spread mixture on each biscuit.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes until brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields 20 pieces.

title: buttermilk baked chicken(also good with cubed steak)
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Melt margarine in a skillet (one that can be put in the oven).
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk; roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Put in skillet and brown slightly on both sides on top of range.
Then bake in oven 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat yolks, adding milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add margarine and cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour into crust.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill. Serves 9 to 12.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Set aside.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Slowly add scalded milk while beating.
Put in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water, beating constantly.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat and cool.
Add vanilla and cream.
Pour mixture into freezer container, filling not more than 3/4 full.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer instructions.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: marinated fried turkey
directions: Inject turkey all over and set overnight.

title: chicken fettucine
directions: Skin chicken breast and cut into thin strips.
Drain and chop tomatoes (unless diced).
Thaw frozen peas.

title: potato and sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine potatoes, sauerkraut and eggs.
Toss lightly and chill.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly but thoroughly. Serve chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In mixing bowl, beat egg, mix in brown and white sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix.
Add vanilla, then mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in bowl.
Add 7-Up last, then ice and fruit slices.
Serves 50.
(Makes 7 1/4 quarts.)

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Place the cranberries, sugar and water in a heavy saucepan. Bring to the boil, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved.
Reduce heat and simmer until the berries break open and the liquid is reduced a bit.
Remove from heat.
Add cinnamon and orange peel.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown beef in large skillet over low heat.
Stir occasionally. Add 2 cups water, bouillon cube and butter.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in Spanish rice mix.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut peppers in half, lengthwise.
Remove seeds and simmer in boiling salted water 10 minutes.
Fill peppers with rice mixture and place in shallow baking dish.
Mix tomato sauce with remaining water and pour over rice.
Top with cheese and heat under broiler.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put beef in roaster.
Combine rest of ingredients, except brown sugar, and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 300° for 6 hours or until meat shreds.
May need to add more water as meat cooks.
Now, add brown sugar to taste, if you want.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
May be cooked ahead and frozen for later use.

title: tiala (tee-a-la)
directions: Slice squash and potatoes thick.
Precook to reduce baking time.
Fry ground meat, seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Drain off fat.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat milk with egg.
Blend dry ingredients and gradually add to milk mixture.
Beat constantly until batter is smooth.

title: john's crepe suzette
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat yolks.
Add milk, dry ingredients, lemon rind and, lastly, the stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: tijuana taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine refried beans, 3 tablespoons tomato sauce and 1/2 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with chopped tomato and Monterey Jack cheese.

title: mary glynn's soda bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender; work well.
Mix eggs well with buttermilk; add soda dissolved in small amount of buttermilk.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead only until smooth.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in 9-inch greased cake pan at 350°.
Cool covered lightly for 30 minutes with cloth. Slice when completely cool.

title: black fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, beat well.
Sift flour and spices, baking powder and soda.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a cookie sheet with shortening. Heat margarine until melted.
Set aside.
Stir flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, the baking powder and salt in a medium bowl. Stir in milk and 3 tablespoons of the melted margarine until dough forms.

title: cookie kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add brown sugar and flour gradually.
Add vanilla; fold in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls well apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add well beaten eggs, dry ingredients and mashed bananas. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: saltwater taffy
directions: Butter a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; set pan aside.
Butter the sides of a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.

title: apple raisin muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and spice.
Set aside. Combine milk, egg and margarine.
Beat until blended.
Add flour mixture and mix until blended but lumpy.
Stir in chopped apples and raisins.
Spoon batter into 14 non-stick muffin pans (about 2/3 full) and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until muffins are golden.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 14 muffins, 105 calories each.

title: corn 'n' rice pudding
directions: In an 8-inch square baking pan, combine corn, rice, milk, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cut cheese and bacon in 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Combine 1 1/4 cups of Cheddar cheese, 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese and all remaining ingredients.
Toss with the spaghetti.
Place in greased casserole and sprinkle with reserved cheeses.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy chicken and rice slow cooker
directions: In a slow cooker combine mushrooms, celery, onion dill weed and pepper.
Top with chicken.
Pour soup and broth over chicken. Cover, cook on High 2 1/2 to 3 hours or Low 5 to 6 hours.
If using low turn slow cooker to high heat setting.
Stir uncooked rice into mushroom mixture.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes more.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Add dash of salt.
Add vanilla and almond.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cover with glaze (confectioners sugar and lemon juice).

title: grandmama dodd's chewy brownies
directions: Mix and spread onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, crushed pecans and margarine or butter (at room temperature).
Cook at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: summer days iced tea
directions: Boil the water.
Stir in sugar.
Add tea bags, cloves and mint. Let steep for 20 minutes.
Remove the tea bags and mint and add the lemon juice.
Chill or add ice and enjoy.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat canned milk, flavoring, salt and sugar for 2 minutes. Pour into chilled gallon size churn.
Fill churn to fill line with whole milk.

title: whole wheat pizza crust
directions: Mix the flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir in oil and water until smooth.
Add enough flour or water to make soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured surface; knead for 2 to 3 minutes, until smooth.
Press into greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Use fingers to press up sides of pan.
Continue with your favorite ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's lemon cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles according to package directions and drain.
Layer starting with cheese, then macaroni, then finish with cheese.
Beat and add eggs, buttermilk or milk and salt. Cover all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Layer 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish with tortillas.
Place some of the chicken on top of tortillas.
Mix salsa and soups together with half a can of water.
Pour soup mixture over chicken, then repeat with layers of tortillas, chicken and soup mixture.
Final layer will be tortillas.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake covered for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes a nice dish for potlucks.

title: clam-filled lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine reserved clam liquid and spaghetti sauce.
Reserving 1 cup sauce, spoon remainder equally into individual ramekins or 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine clams, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley; mix well.
Spread equal portions on lasagna strips; roll up jellyroll fashion.
Place seam side down in ramekins.
Top with remaining sauce; cover.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until hot.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cabbage onion salad(serves 24)
directions: Alternate cabbage and onions in a bowl with onions for top layer.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add oil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening. Add baking soda in water, eggs, salt and vanilla. Slowly add the flour. When well mixed, add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: easy peach pie
directions: In a saucepan bring sugar, water, cornstarch and food coloring to a boil until thick.
Remove from heat and add peach flavored Jell-o.
Cool.
When cool, pour over sliced peaches in pie shell. Chill until ready to serve.
Top each serving with Cool Whip.

title: bernie arnold's chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak as thinly as possible and cut in crosswise pieces (for easier cutting, cut meat when partially thawed).

title: nellie's nut bread
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
This bread will rise while baking and then fall.
When it falls, remove from oven as the bread will be hard if overcooked.
Slice and serve.

title: vegetable clam chowder
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add juice from strained clams.
Put in vegetables, dry vegetables, butter and salt pork.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add seasonings and clams; stir in half and half and cheese.
While soup is still hot, stir in instant mashed potatoes to desired thickness.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: vanilla butter
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in vanilla until mix is smooth.
Chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In large skillet, brown onions, celery and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, mashed potatoes and flour.
Add flour until dough is too stiff to stir.
Then turn on to floured board and knead.
Put into greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out. Spread margarine over dough with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple creme pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Stir constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Spoon into cooled pastry shell.
Spread meringue atop pie, sealing meringue to edge of pastry.
Cool before cutting.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil and debone fryers.
Make a dark roux of flour and oil. To the roux, add vegetables, chopped.
Let cook until just tender; add vegetables to a large soup kettle.
Add tomatoes, broth and some water.
Boil 1 1/2 hours, then add meat and the herbs.
Cook 10 minutes.
Can add shrimp, too.
Serve over rice in soup bowl. Yield:
12 servings.

title: f.c.e. soup and cornbread soup
directions: Cook stew beef with pepper in 1 gallon of water.
Add onions when meat gets about done, then add chopped tomatoes, other vegetables, salt and sugar.
Cook until vegies are tender.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° until done. Mix 1 stick softened margarine with a box of confectioners sugar and strawberries to make icing.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until well mixed, then add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Separate an egg and add yolk to the leftover mashed potatoes. Beat the egg white well and add that next.
Turn into a shallow baking dish and dot with butter.
Heat and brown in a hot oven.

title: ruby red strawberry burst
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend for a few seconds on high speed or until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Pour into a large glass.
Garnish with a strawberry sliced halfway and placed on rim of glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Soak gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Heat contents of pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Let come to a boil.
Add gelatin and cool.
When congealing, add cheese and Cool Whip. Pour into Pyrex dish and allow to set.

title: jimmy's potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients (except milk) in crock pot or slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
(If cooking on high setting let cook 3 to 4 hour.)
During last hour of cooking, stir in milk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vegetable oil, vanilla and grated raw zucchini.
Combine baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, flour and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add walnuts and raisins.
Mix all and pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack or serve warm.

title: creamy garlic dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine oil, sour cream, heavy cream, vinegar, salt and garlic until smooth.
Chill.
Serve over salad greens.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 1 2/3 cup.

title: scalloped clams
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl; blend until thoroughly mixed.
Place in lightly buttered 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: flannel cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, beat egg well.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Add flour all at once and mix.
Dissolve the 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda in about 1 tablespoon of lukewarm water.
Add to batter.
Heat griddle to 450° and lightly oil or grease.
Drop by 1/4 cup on griddle.
Bake as any other pancake.
When bubbles form on top side and is evenly brown underneath, turn and brown the other side.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix all soups, water and rice.
Pour over chicken breasts; bake at 350° in baking dish.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put into a buttered/greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread/cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and begins to brown on top.
Can also use turkey in place of chicken and also can use asparagus in place of broccoli.

title: chili casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain grease. Stir in beans, tomato sauce, tomatoes, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in noodles and heat through. Yield: 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a full boil.
Measure other ingredients while stirring syrup every few minutes.
Put the corn flakes in a big bowl that will not melt.
When the sugar and syrup comes to a full boil, remove it from the heat and stir in peanut butter and butter.
Mix until melted.
Pour mixture over the corn flakes and mix until all the flakes are well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool.
Store in covered container.
Makes 40 to 60, depending on size.

title: apple cream pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute apples, sugar and lemon juice in butter until apples are tender. Cool. In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in 1 cup milk, dry pudding mix and lemon peel. Add remaining milk; beat until thickened. Spread into pastry shell. Arrange apples over filling. Brush with preserves. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving. Brush with additional preserves if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: great zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, peppers and onions with salt.
Let stand overnight, then drain well.
Combine vegetables with all remaining ingredients, blending well.
In a large pot, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Mix together and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked apple pork chops
directions: Brown chops and place in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and sage.
Lay apple wedges over top. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Make gravy with flour and drippings, adding water, vinegar and salt to taste.
Stir until thick.
Pour over chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter, add soup, broth, chilies, sour cream, add chicken.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Place 1/3 cheese into 9x13 inch casserole.
Top with layers of tortilla pieces, sauce and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Do not grease pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Use as a side dish for chili, ham or pork dishes.

title: jello pistachio cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased, floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato and carrot casserole
directions: Peel and slice both potatoes and carrots.
Cook in a separate saucepan until done.
Mix ham, onions and garlic together; brown until done.
Place in a casserole dish a layer each of potatoes, carrots and ham.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 cup of juice from cooked carrots.
Pour this over casserole.
Slice cheese and place over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: swedish vasa apple cake
directions: Note:
I add 1/2 cup moistened raisins.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400°.

title: sad when gone cake
directions: Mix Bisquick with brown sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add oil, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and serve.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add shortening, peanut butter and egg, beating until well blended. Gradually add sifted ingredients and mix well.
Add peanut butter chips, stirring to blend.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten balls with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool on cookie sheets.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots; drain.
Make sauce from remaining ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
In casserole dish, layer carrots and cheese slices, ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hiker bars
directions: In large saucepan, stir in brown sugar and honey. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly and remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Stir in whole grain cereal flakes. Stir in mixed dried fruit bits until well coated. Spread into greased pan. Press reserved fruit bits on top. Cool. Cut into bars and wrap each in plastic wrap. Makes 24 bars.

title: honey bran bread
directions: Mix All-Bran, shortening and boiling water and allow shortening to melt.
In separate bowl, beat well the eggs, honey, salt and soda.
Combine all ingredients and add flour.
let rise in bowl 1 1/2 hours.
Place in 2 large or 3 medium greased loaf pans and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350°, medium loaves for approximately 30 minutes and large loaves for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Make a crust of margarine, flour and pecans.
Mix and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; press down lightly.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°; cool.

title: calavasita(a mexican chili stew)
directions: Fry bacon and remove to drain.
In hot bacon drippings, sear beef and pork until very brown.
Add chopped onions and peppers; simmer.
Add bacon, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin seed, squash, salt and pepper.
If needed, add a small amount of water to keep the stew from sticking to the bottom of the pot.
Cover and simmer for 2 or 3 hours; no need to stir.
Add corn and simmer for an additional 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Combine onion, mayonnaise, eggs and soup in large bowl; mix well. Stir in broccoli. Spoon into 9-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Put a nut or cherry half in the center. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lone star beer roast
directions: Sprinkle both sides of roast well with lemon pepper and place roast in roaster or pan; marinate roast overnight in 1 can of beer, 1 bottle Wish-Bone dressing and cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast and top with garlic.
Do not salt until done.
Bake at 350°, covered or wrapped in foil, until done (160° internal temperature), about 2 hours.
Last 30 minutes, I place potatoes and carrots around roast and continue baking until done. When done, remove to serving platter.

title: mother's cheese ball
directions: Remove cheeses from refrigerator and let warm to room temperature.
Mix cheeses and onion with mixer until combined. Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Make a thick paste of the flour and some milk.
Gradually add rest of milk.
Cook in double boiler, beating constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add vanilla and beat until fluffy. Add cooled milk mixture and continue beating until like whipped cream. Cool before icing cake.
Cake and icing must be cool.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil to soft boil stage. Add: 1 tsp. vanilla & 1/2 tsp. cream of tartar. Pour over 6 cups Pecans. Mix well. Pour on waxed paper, separate and let cool.

title: ann landers meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce and bacon strips. Press into loaf pan.
Cover with the bacon strips, if desired. Pour the tomato sauce over mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: breaded chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breast halves to 1/4-inch thick between Saran Wrap using rolling pin.
Mix egg, mustard and milk in bowl with fork; set aside.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in bowl with fork. Set aside.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in bowl with fork.
Set aside.
Dip chicken pieces first in flour mixture, then in egg mixture, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken on platter in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Heat 3/4-inch oil in electric frypan at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove chicken from refrigerator. Cook in oil until brown on both sides (approximately 5 minutes on each side).
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: dairy queen blizzard
directions: Freeze candy bar.
Break the candy into tiny pieces with a knife handle before removing wrapper.
Combine all of the ingredients in the blender and blend for 30 seconds on medium speed.
Stop the blender to stir the mixture with a spoon; repeat until well mixed.
Pour into a 16 ounce glass.

title: aunt magdeline's lemon pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy. Add flavoring and zest; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Mix flours and mix lemon juice and milk. Add flour and wet ingredients alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Do not overmix this part, just mix enough to make sure each is incorporated. Pour into buttered and floured large Bundt pan. Place into cold oven; turn on to 300° and bake for about 1 hour and 45 minutes. Do not open oven during the first 1 hour and 15 minutes after baking. You may check it after this time by gently opening the oven and placing a toothpick into the center. If clean when removed, the cake is done. Allow to cool about 10 minutes and extract from pan after cooling.

title: delicious li'l smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer in crock-pot or covered pan on stove.

title: golden refresher punch
directions: Combine water, cloves and cinnamon in a medium size saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes.
Refrigerate until very cold.
Combine this syrup with all the other ingredients except sherbet.

title: lazy boy fruit pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, butter and milk.
Pour into long cake pan.
Cook rhubarb, sweetened to taste.
Pour into middle of pan.
Cook until done.

title: lime sherbet
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar and lemon juice. When cool, add milk.
Freeze.
If needed, beat with mixer until smooth.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Partially freeze steak.
Slice across grain into thin strips.
Combine flour and pepper, mixing well.
Dredge meat in flour mixture; set aside.
Coat a small Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and onions to Dutch oven.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Remove vegetables from Dutch oven and set aside.
Add meat to Dutch oven. Increase heat to medium-high and cook until browned.
Stir in mushrooms, onion and remaining ingredients, except yogurt and noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in yogurt.
Cook meat and sauce until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Serve over noodles.

title: stir-fried shrimp
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil for 1 minute.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, onion and wine; stir until shrimp are pink and vegetables are hot.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Can use any meat you wish as a substitute (bacon, ham, etc.).

title: coney island chili sauce
directions: Saute onion.
Add meat and cook.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cook until thick.

title: hamburg quiche
directions: Saute hamburg, onions and peppers.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg, pepper and dry mustard.
Add cooked hamburg mixture.
Pour in pie crust.
Add cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until set and cheese is browned.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Grease pan and place rolls 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Add vanilla, stir in flour and salt; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: couch potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in half lengthwise but not all the way through, leaving potato attached at the bottom.
Push potatoes open and fluff pulp with a fork.
Place on a microwave safe plate.
Top each with the chili, onions, mushrooms, ham and cheese.
Cover and microwave on high for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with sour cream if desired.
Serves 2.

title: ann's quick dip
directions: Melt together in a saucepan over medium heat the chili and cubed Velveeta cheese, stirring frequently.
Serve with chips for dipping.

title: tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise and onions.
For each sandwich, top English muffin half with lettuce, tomato slice and tuna mixture. Place on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Broil 1 minute.
Top with cheese slice.
Broil for 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt. Makes 4 sandwiches.
Each sandwich contains:
1.5 grams fat and 200 calories.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Put butter in the bottom of a long cake pan.
Put a layer of potatoes, then layer with onions, salt and pepper.
Then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Make another layer; then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Drain 2 cans pineapple and 1 can peaches.
Mix juice with instant pudding.
Pour over fruit from the cans.
Then drain juice from other fruits (discard other fruit juice, don't add any more juice to the mixture).
If you use frozen fruit, thaw completely. Drain before adding to mixture.
Mixture will keep two weeks.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Cut the greens off the carrots.
Juice the carrots and reserve 2 cups of the pulp.
In a large skillet, heat the 1 tablespoon olive oil over low heat.
Add the onion and zucchini and saut until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.
In a small saucepan over high heat, boil the water.
Remove the saucepan from the heat and add the bouillon cube, tamari and curry.
When the cube is dissolved, stir the hot broth.
In a large bowl, combine the hot broth and TVP.
Let the mixture sit until the TVP is hydrated (10 minutes).
Add the pulp and sunflower seeds and mix with spoon or hands.
Add the sauted vegetables and green onion and mix again.
Mix in salt.
Pinch off a small piece of the mixture and form balls.
In a large skillet, pour in just enough of the remaining oil to coat the bottom.
Add the meatballs and cook them over low heat, turning to keep them from sticking, until golden brown on all sides, for 12 minutes.
Remove from skillet with a slotted spoon.

title: cornish pastries
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll crust thin (use pastry recipe Cream Cheese Pastry).
Place 1/2 tablespoon mixture in center of pastry. Fold into a roll.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 115 small rolls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat pudding mix, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice until smooth and thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover; freeze.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: save-a-penny casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in soup, spaghetti and vegetables.

Transfer to ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. If desired, sprinkle with cheese and let stand a few minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add liquid ingredients.
Beat well and pour in two greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked crust.
Sprinkle freshly grated nutmeg over top and bake at 300° until filling is set, about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swiss steak
directions: Put a little oil in frying pan.
Add bell pepper and onion and brown.
Flour round steaks, then add salt and pepper.
Put in pan and brown.
Pour 1 small can tomato sauce in and add water. Simmer for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brunch sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place croutons and cheese in the bottom of a greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain if needed.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm in center.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: golden au gratin potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup butter, onion and salt.
Stir in potatoes and cheese.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss cornflakes and remaining butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread a thin layer on each tortilla shell and roll up.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours.
Cut into pinwheels and serve with taco sauce.

title: single lemon bars
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in skillet; toss in bread and cracker crumbs coating with butter.
Spread half crumbs over bottom of baking dish.
Drain oysters (keep liquid) and arrange in single layers over crumbs.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix dash of Tabasco with the cream and 2 tablespoons of oyster liquid.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: jewish brownies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients with a spoon.
After mixing, bake in greased broiler pan at 325° for 20 minutes. Combine coconut and condensed milk.
Spread gently over hot cake.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.

title: albongidas(mexican meatball soup)
directions: Chop onion, 1/2 bunch cilantro, garlic and bell pepper.
Add long grain rice.
Add hamburger meat and mix well.
Shape into meatballs, about 1-inch diameter.
Set aside.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and arrange in greased 8x11 inch pan.
Place chicken slices on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: rice breakfast bake
directions: Combine rice and sausage.
Spoon rice into a greased shallow baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over rice mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut in squares and serve.
We like salsa spooned over the top.

title: biscotti(italian tea cookie)
directions: Beat 5 eggs.
Add sugar and blend.
Sift flour and add baking powder. Add to eggs and sugar mixture. Add anise oil and softened margarine.
Mix well.
Knead until dough is smooth. Roll dough into oblong shape 3/4-inch thick. Brush 1 beaten egg over mixture. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased pan at 350° for 14 minutes until brown.

title: dill oyster crackers
directions: Mix all together and stir into oyster crackers.
Stir about 5 times, once every hour.
Put in tight covered containers.
tags: Hidden Valley salad dressing dry mix

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together, layer in a serving dish with tomato, lettuce and cheddar cheese.

title: strawberry preserves made with figs
directions: Combine sugar, figs and gelatin in a pot and bring to a boil. Turn heat down to a minimum and cook for at least 15 minutes. Remove pot from burner.
Place mixture in jars and seal with wax.

title: baked apples
directions: With a paring knife, core apples and stand them, bottom down, in a baking dish.
Spread a thin layer of honey inside and on top of the apple.
Sprinkle cinnamon to taste, making sure some gets inside the apples.
Stuff raisins into the center of the apples. Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until apple skins start to split.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: savory pork stir-fry
directions: Slice pork or chicken across grain in 1/8-inch strips. Marinate in soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, sesame oil, garlic and ginger for 10 minutes.
Heat vegetable oil in electric skillet or wok to 400°.
Stir-fry pork for 3 to 5 minutes, until pork is no longer pink.
Add vegetables, chicken broth and marinade.
Stir mixture until tender-crisp.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine vegetables and cheese.
Mix sugar, water, oil, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and let set overnight. Mix several times.
Just before serving, add croutons and mix once again.

title: corn flake cookies - no bake
directions: Bring to boil over low heat, Karo syrup and white sugar. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oleo.
Mix well.
Pour over corn flakes and walnuts.
Mix to coat.
Drop on cookie sheet. Cool and enjoy.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix together well and keep in fridge.

title: green salad
directions: Mix pudding and sour cream together.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Can be frozen or refrigerated.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Put half of vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Spread mixture into wafers.
Spread strawberries over top.
Spread whipped cream next; top with remaining crushed wafers. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: gravy
directions: Mix grease and flour.
Heat until mixture starts to brown. Reduce heat and add Milnot.
Fill can with water.
Add water, heat until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
I use a wire whisk after adding Milnot and water to prevent lumps.

title: double chocolate souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat inside of 2 1/2-quart souffle dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Separate eggs, placing yolks in small bowl and whites in large bowl.
Place milk, sugar, flour and salt in 2-cup jar with lid.
Shake until smooth.
Pour into saucepan; stir in cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Stir a little hot mixture into yolks; stir yolks back into saucepan.
Beat together egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed until stiff, but not dry, peaks form.
Gently but thoroughly fold yolk mixture and chocolate pieces into whites. With a rubber spatula, cut down through center of whites, across bottom of bowl and up side, turning bowl as you fold.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until puffy and souffle shakes slightly when rack is gently moved.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Make Stove Top stuffing according to directions.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Add food coloring, vanilla and vinegar. Mix well. Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and cocoa. Blend the dry ingredients with the cream mixture. Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans (greased). Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crabby mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat with lemon juice in medium bowl.
Add the next five ingredients and mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Rinse a baking sheet lightly with water, shaking off excess.
Arrange mushrooms on sheet.
Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking until tips are golden, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: marianne's meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Tear bread into pieces and place in a large bowl. Add milk and egg. Add meat and seasonings; mix well. Form lightly into loaf shape; place in shallow baking pan. Bake 1 hour.Can put catsup and/or include cheese cubes or stuffed olives.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Bring the carrots, with
water	to cover, to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Drain
and
cool.
In
medium-sized bowl, mix the salt, pepper and mustard.
Beat
in a little of the oil to blend with the mustard.
Add
remaining oil and sugar, vinegar and soup and beat again	to
blend
well.
Stir	in the cooled carrots, onion and
green	pepper.
Cover	tightly
and
chill overnight.	Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook roast and onion in a pressure cooker until very tender. Remove meat from pot and shred meat with a fork until very thin. Return to crock-pot; add other ingredients.
Cook overnight on low temperature.
Salt and pepper to taste.
This can be frozen for later use.
Very good at Christmastime.

title: tuna cream dip
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add salt, sour cream, chopped pickle and green onions; mix well.
Garnish with parsley (optional).
Serve with crackers, potato chips or cut up vegetables of your choice.

title: oven barbecue shrimp
directions: Rinse shrimp.
Place in oblong baking dish.
In small saucepan, mix butter, paprika, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, seafood seasonings and garlic salt.
Cook until well blended. Pour over shrimp.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated oven at 425°. Turn shrimp over and bake 10 more minutes.
Serve.
Cook corn and potatoes in water to which a packet of shrimp boil has been added.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender; salt to taste.
Drain and cool.
Chop green pepper and onion.
In large bowl, combine soup, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce; mix well by hand.
Use glass bowl; place carrots, green pepper and onions in layers.
Pour marinade over all.
Cover tightly; let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour half into a large bowl or 8-cup mold.
Set in fridge.
Take out when set and spread all of sour cream over jello.
Pour remaining jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Return to fridge and allow to set up.
Take out of mold or bowl onto plate.

title: green chili squares
directions: Use 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Put half grated cheese in pan. Layer chili pepper on top, then another layer of cheese.
Beat eggs, add chili powder, chili juice and paprika.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Can be frozen.
Heat in oven 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bahamian conch chowder
directions: Wash, drain and dice conch.
Cook bacon.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Pour all ingredients in Dutch oven to cook with 2 quarts of water for 3 1/2 hours or until done.
Season with hot sauce or Worcestershire sauce.

title: 3-layer mexican dip
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
On a 16-ounce platter, layer the bean dip for first layer, avocado dip for second layer and sour cream mixture for third layer.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with corn chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients separately.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix with broccoli and marinate.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Crust:
Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
(Be certain sides of pan are 1-inch high.)
Beat flour, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt into coarse crumbs.
Press firmly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: full meal beans
directions: *All 3 must be the same size.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Put in baking dish. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle pecans on top of dip and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Drain Veg-All and mix with celery and chicken soups.
Add 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth. Mix in a bowl.
Chop chicken and line casserole dish.
Pour vegetable mixture over chicken.

title: oven fried chicken and potatoes
directions: Brown chicken and put in casserole dish.
Place peeled potatoes over the chicken.
Mix all the remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and potatoes.
Place in oven at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: plain scotch scones
directions: Fold butter into dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk.
Mix well.
Put on a floured board; pat down until 1/2-inch thick, then cut into triangles.
Cook in electric frypan at 375°, until brown on both sides.
Makes 8 to 10.
Serve with butter, jams or jelly.

title: grandma's brown bread
directions: Mix together sugar and shortening. Add egg, flour, salt and baking soda.
Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes.
Add raisins to rest of ingredients (water, too), when raisins cool.
Pour in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add flavorings. Pour into a large tube pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and pour over broccoli flowerets, onion, sunflower seeds and bacon pieces.
Do not stir. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: banana dessert
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, 6 tablespoons melted butter and sugar. Spread into pan.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla together until fluffy and spread over cookie mix.
Roll bananas in lemon juice.
Put on top of mix.
Drain pineapple.
Combine with one large container of Cool Whip.
Spread over bananas.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix pumpkin and eggs together on medium speed with mixer.
Mix in sugar, milk and spices.
Pour into pan.
Mix together cake mix and butter to form crumb mixture. Spread over pumpkin. Top with nuts and press down gently.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl combine the Jell-O and hot water.
Add the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch glass dish.
Chill until set.
Soften the cream cheese and mix well with the sugar.
Blend in the sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over the Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars and margarine in microwave.
Let cool.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Chocolate lover's dream!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup crushed chips.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cover with 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: hot fudge sauce(microwave)
directions: Heat chocolate chips and corn syrup 4 to 4 1/2 minutes on power level 5.
Gradually add milk; stir in vanilla and margarine.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar in mixer on very low power until evenly mixed.
Melt chocolate and add chocolate and vanilla to mixture. Mix thoroughly until even.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix on medium power for 5 minutes after adding each egg.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours (approximately) before eating.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Combine oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce. Wash spinach and add chopped onion.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and add to spinach.
Slice eggs; add to spinach. Pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Cook
hamburger
and onion together.
Cook cup of rice. Mix all
ingredients
together except Chinese noodles.	Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Then add Chinese noodles on top and bake 20 minutes uncovered at 300°.

title: zesty tuna salad
directions: Cut off and discard the large (tasteless) base of the celery stalks and chop the remainder into small pieces, including the leaves.
Use a red bell pepper if possible.
(Yellow will do and green is okay, if the others are not available.)
Cut the pepper into small cubes.
The important thing for this salad is to blend all of the ingredients thoroughly.
Drain the tuna and place in a large salad bowl (you'll need room for blending).
Blend in the lime juice, then the horseradish.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in the sweet relish.
Add the parsley, onions, celery and bell pepper, one ingredient at a time, and mix thoroughly after each addition. Serve with your favorite crackers and beer.
This recipe will serve, all by itself, as a hardy meal for 2 hungry adults.
Any leftovers can be safely stored in the refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add egg and mix.
In large bowl, mix together flour, salt, nutmeg, cloves, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, shortening and oatmeal. Mix well and add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: onion baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces. Dice the onions and mix the two together.
Prepare 6 sets of foil.
Place the potatoes and onions on the foil (equivalent of one potato).
Place pads of margarine over mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap each set and bake at 450° until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and salt for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and stir quickly.
Pour into well buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.
Wrap to stay moist.

title: fudge
directions: In saucepan, place milk, sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling over a low heat; cook 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and celery in one stick of butter; add Cheez Whiz and soups.
Melt slowly.
Add rice, broccoli and water chestnuts.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs and drizzle with 1/2 stick butter over top.
Bake until bubbly. Freezes well.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat with a mixer or spoon until smooth butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Now beat in flour mixture with mixer until smooth.
Chill 1 hour until firm.
Roll a small amount of dough at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Use floured board.
Cut dough in desired shapes with floured cookie cutter.
Put on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 minutes or until brown.
Remove to wire heat rack to cool.
Decorate with your favorite colored frostings.

title: vegetable rice bake
directions: Bring bouillon granules and 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a saucepan; add rice.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until rice is tender.
In a medium saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water and green pepper; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini or broccoli.
Cover; simmer for 3 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender; drain well.
Set aside.
